lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mnflet: 
   shows "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ \<cmnf> \<lsq> A"
proof -
   have S1: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_nltmnft)
   have S2: "\<cmnf> ∈ ℝ⇧*" by (rule MMI_mnfxr)
   have S3: "( \<cmnf> ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ A ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( \<cmnf> \<lsq> A ⟷ ¬ ( A \<ls> \<cmnf> ) )" by (rule MMI_xrlenltt)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( \<cmnf> \<lsq> A ⟷ ¬ ( A \<ls> \<cmnf> ) )" by (rule MMI_mpan)
   from S1 S4 show "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ \<cmnf> \<lsq> A" by (rule MMI_mpbird)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_xrltnsymt: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A \<ls> B ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶   
 ( A \<ls> B ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_ltnsymt)
   have S2: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ A ∈ ℝ⇧*" by (rule MMI_rexrt)
   have S3: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ¬ ( \<cpnf> \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_pnfnltt)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ ¬ ( \<cpnf> \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S4 have S5: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ ¬ ( \<cpnf> \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   have S6: "B = \<cpnf> ⟶ ( B \<ls> A ⟷ \<cpnf> \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_breq1)
   from S6 have S7: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ ( B \<ls> A ⟷ \<cpnf> \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S5 S7 have S8: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_mtbird)
   from S8 have S9: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B =   
 \<cpnf> ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_a1d)
   from S2 have S10: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ A ∈ ℝ⇧*" .
   have S11: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_nltmnft)
   from S10 S11 have S12: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S12 have S13: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   have S14: "B = \<cmnf> ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟷ A \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_breq2)
   from S14 have S15: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟷ A \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S13 S15 have S16: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> B )" by (rule MMI_mtbird)
   from S16 have S17: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B =   
 \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_pm2_21d)
   from S1 S9 S17 have S18: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ ( B ∈ ℝ ∨ B = \<cpnf> ∨ B = \<cmnf> ) ) ⟶   
 ( A \<ls> B ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_3jaodan)
   have S19: "B ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ¬ ( \<cpnf> \<ls> B )" by (rule MMI_pnfnltt)
   from S19 have S20: "( A = \<cpnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶ ¬ ( \<cpnf> \<ls> B )" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   have S21: "A = \<cpnf> ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟷ \<cpnf> \<ls> B )" by (rule MMI_breq1)
   from S21 have S22: "( A = \<cpnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟷ \<cpnf> \<ls> B )" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   from S20 S22 have S23: "( A = \<cpnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> B )" by (rule MMI_mtbird)
   from S23 have S24: "( A =   
 \<cpnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_pm2_21d)
   have S25: "B ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟷ ( B ∈ ℝ ∨ B = \<cpnf> ∨ B = \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_elxr)
   from S24 S25 have S26: "( A =   
 \<cpnf> ∧ ( B ∈ ℝ ∨ B =   
 \<cpnf> ∨ B =   
 \<cmnf> ) ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_sylan2br)
   have S27: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ B ∈ ℝ⇧*" by (rule MMI_rexrt)
   have S28: "B ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_nltmnft)
   from S27 S28 have S29: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S29 have S30: "( A = \<cmnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   have S31: "A = \<cmnf> ⟶ ( B \<ls> A ⟷ B \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_breq2)
   from S31 have S32: "( A = \<cmnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ ( B \<ls> A ⟷ B \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   from S30 S32 have S33: "( A = \<cmnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_mtbird)
   from S33 have S34: "( A =   
 \<cmnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_a1d)
   have S35: "\<cmnf> ∈ ℝ⇧*" by (rule MMI_mnfxr)
   have S36: "\<cmnf> ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ¬ ( \<cpnf> \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_pnfnltt)
   from S35 S36 have S37: "¬ ( \<cpnf> \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_ax_mp)
   have S38: "( B = \<cpnf> ∧ A = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ( B \<ls> A ⟷ \<cpnf> \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_breq12)
   from S37 S38 have S39: "( B = \<cpnf> ∧ A = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_mtbiri)
   from S39 have S40: "( A = \<cmnf> ∧ B = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_ancoms)
   from S40 have S41: "( A =   
 \<cmnf> ∧ B = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_a1d)
   have S42: "\<cmnf> ∈ ℝ⇧*" by (rule MMI_mnfxr)
   have S43: "\<cmnf> ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ¬ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_xrltnrt)
   from S42 S43 have S44: "¬ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_ax_mp)
   have S45: "( A = \<cmnf> ∧ B = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟷ \<cmnf> \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_breq12)
   from S44 S45 have S46: "( A = \<cmnf> ∧ B = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> B )" by (rule MMI_mtbiri)
   from S46 have S47: "( A =   
 \<cmnf> ∧ B = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_pm2_21d)
   from S34 S41 S47 have S48: "( A =   
 \<cmnf> ∧ ( B ∈ ℝ ∨ B =   
 \<cpnf> ∨ B =   
 \<cmnf> ) ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_3jaodan)
   from S18 S26 S48 have S49: "( ( A ∈ ℝ ∨ A = \<cpnf> ∨ A = \<cmnf> ) ∧ ( B ∈ ℝ ∨ B = \<cpnf> ∨ B = \<cmnf> ) ) ⟶   
 ( A \<ls> B ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_3jaoian)
   have S50: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟷ ( A ∈ ℝ ∨ A = \<cpnf> ∨ A = \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_elxr)
   from S25 have S51: "B ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟷ ( B ∈ ℝ ∨ B = \<cpnf> ∨ B = \<cmnf> )" .
   from S49 S50 S51 show "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A \<ls> B ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_syl2anb)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_xrlttrit: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A \<ls> B ⟷ ¬ ( ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ) ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_xrltnrt)
   from S1 have S2: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ A = B ) ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   have S3: "A = B ⟶ ( A \<ls> A ⟷ A \<ls> B )" by (rule MMI_breq2)
   from S3 have S4: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ A = B ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> A ⟷ A \<ls> B )" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S2 S4 have S5: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ A = B ) ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> B )" by (rule MMI_mtbid)
   from S5 have S6: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( A = B ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) )" by (rule MMI_ex)
   from S6 have S7: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A = B ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) )" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   have S8: "( B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ A ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( B \<ls> A ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) )" by (rule MMI_xrltnsymt)
   from S8 have S9: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( B \<ls> A ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) )" by (rule MMI_ancoms)
   from S7 S9 have S10: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ) ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) )" by (rule MMI_jaod)
   have S11: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶   
 ( A \<ls> B ⟷ ¬ ( ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ) ) )" by (rule MMI_axlttri)
   from S11 have S12: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶   
 ( ¬ ( ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ) ) ⟶ A \<ls> B )" by (rule MMI_biimprd)
   from S12 have S13: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶   
 ( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_con1d)
   have S14: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ A \<ls> \<cpnf>" by (rule MMI_ltpnft)
   from S14 have S15: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ A \<ls> \<cpnf>" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   have S16: "B = \<cpnf> ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟷ A \<ls> \<cpnf> )" by (rule MMI_breq2)
   from S16 have S17: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟷ A \<ls> \<cpnf> )" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S15 S17 have S18: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ A \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_mpbird)
   from S18 have S19: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B =   
 \<cpnf> ) ⟶   
 ( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_pm2_21nd)
   have S20: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ \<cmnf> \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_mnfltt)
   from S20 have S21: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ \<cmnf> \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   have S22: "B = \<cmnf> ⟶ ( B \<ls> A ⟷ \<cmnf> \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_breq1)
   from S22 have S23: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ( B \<ls> A ⟷ \<cmnf> \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S21 S23 have S24: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ B \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_mpbird)
   have S25: "B \<ls> A ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_olc)
   from S24 S25 have S26: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S26 have S27: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B =   
 \<cmnf> ) ⟶   
 ( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_a1d)
   from S13 S19 S27 have S28: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ ( B ∈ ℝ ∨ B = \<cpnf> ∨ B = \<cmnf> ) ) ⟶   
 ( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_3jaodan)
   have S29: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ B \<ls> \<cpnf>" by (rule MMI_ltpnft)
   from S29 have S30: "( A = \<cpnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ B \<ls> \<cpnf>" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   have S31: "A = \<cpnf> ⟶ ( B \<ls> A ⟷ B \<ls> \<cpnf> )" by (rule MMI_breq2)
   from S31 have S32: "( A = \<cpnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ ( B \<ls> A ⟷ B \<ls> \<cpnf> )" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   from S30 S32 have S33: "( A = \<cpnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ B \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_mpbird)
   from S25 have S34: "B \<ls> A ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A )" .
   from S33 S34 have S35: "( A = \<cpnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S35 have S36: "( A =   
 \<cpnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶   
 ( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_a1d)
   have S37: "( A = \<cpnf> ∧ B = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ A = B" by (rule MMI_eqtr3t)
   have S38: "A = B ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_orc)
   from S37 S38 have S39: "( A = \<cpnf> ∧ B = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S39 have S40: "( A =   
 \<cpnf> ∧ B =   
 \<cpnf> ) ⟶   
 ( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_a1d)
   have S41: "\<cmnf> \<ls> \<cpnf>" by (rule MMI_mnfltpnf)
   have S42: "( B = \<cmnf> ∧ A = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ ( B \<ls> A ⟷ \<cmnf> \<ls> \<cpnf> )" by (rule MMI_breq12)
   from S41 S42 have S43: "( B = \<cmnf> ∧ A = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ B \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_mpbiri)
   from S43 have S44: "( A = \<cpnf> ∧ B = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ B \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_ancoms)
   from S25 have S45: "B \<ls> A ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A )" .
   from S44 S45 have S46: "( A = \<cpnf> ∧ B = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S46 have S47: "( A =   
 \<cpnf> ∧ B =   
 \<cmnf> ) ⟶   
 ( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_a1d)
   from S36 S40 S47 have S48: "( A =   
 \<cpnf> ∧ ( B ∈ ℝ ∨ B =   
 \<cpnf> ∨ B =   
 \<cmnf> ) ) ⟶   
 ( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_3jaodan)
   have S49: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ \<cmnf> \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_mnfltt)
   from S49 have S50: "( A = \<cmnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ \<cmnf> \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   have S51: "A = \<cmnf> ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟷ \<cmnf> \<ls> B )" by (rule MMI_breq1)
   from S51 have S52: "( A = \<cmnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟷ \<cmnf> \<ls> B )" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   from S50 S52 have S53: "( A = \<cmnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ A \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_mpbird)
   from S53 have S54: "( A =   
 \<cmnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶   
 ( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_pm2_21nd)
   have S55: "\<cmnf> \<ls> \<cpnf>" by (rule MMI_mnfltpnf)
   have S56: "( A = \<cmnf> ∧ B = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟷ \<cmnf> \<ls> \<cpnf> )" by (rule MMI_breq12)
   from S55 S56 have S57: "( A = \<cmnf> ∧ B = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ A \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_mpbiri)
   from S57 have S58: "( A =   
 \<cmnf> ∧ B =   
 \<cpnf> ) ⟶   
 ( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_pm2_21nd)
   have S59: "( A = \<cmnf> ∧ B = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ A = B" by (rule MMI_eqtr3t)
   from S38 have S60: "A = B ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A )" .
   from S59 S60 have S61: "( A = \<cmnf> ∧ B = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S61 have S62: "( A =   
 \<cmnf> ∧ B =   
 \<cmnf> ) ⟶   
 ( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_a1d)
   from S54 S58 S62 have S63: "( A =   
 \<cmnf> ∧ ( B ∈ ℝ ∨ B =   
 \<cpnf> ∨ B =   
 \<cmnf> ) ) ⟶   
 ( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_3jaodan)
   from S28 S48 S63 have S64: "( ( A ∈ ℝ ∨ A = \<cpnf> ∨ A = \<cmnf> ) ∧ ( B ∈ ℝ ∨ B = \<cpnf> ∨ B = \<cmnf> ) ) ⟶   
 ( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_3jaoian)
   have S65: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟷ ( A ∈ ℝ ∨ A = \<cpnf> ∨ A = \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_elxr)
   have S66: "B ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟷ ( B ∈ ℝ ∨ B = \<cpnf> ∨ B = \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_elxr)
   from S64 S65 S66 have S67: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ⟶ ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_syl2anb)
   from S10 S67 have S68: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ) ⟷ ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) )" by (rule MMI_impbid)
   from S68 show "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A \<ls> B ⟷ ¬ ( ( A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ) ) )" by (rule MMI_con2bid)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_xrlttrt: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_axlttrn)
   from S1 have S2: "( ( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ∧ C ∈ ℝ ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_3expa)
   from S2 have S3: "( ( A ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_an1rs)
   have S4: "C ∈ ℝ ⟶ C ∈ ℝ⇧*" by (rule MMI_rexrt)
   have S5: "C ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ¬ ( \<cpnf> \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_pnfnltt)
   from S4 S5 have S6: "C ∈ ℝ ⟶ ¬ ( \<cpnf> \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S6 have S7: "( C ∈ ℝ ∧ B = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ ¬ ( \<cpnf> \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   have S8: "B = \<cpnf> ⟶ ( B \<ls> C ⟷ \<cpnf> \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_breq1)
   from S8 have S9: "( C ∈ ℝ ∧ B = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ ( B \<ls> C ⟷ \<cpnf> \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S7 S9 have S10: "( C ∈ ℝ ∧ B = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_mtbird)
   from S10 have S11: "( C ∈ ℝ ∧ B = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ ( B \<ls> C ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_pm2_21d)
   from S11 have S12: "( ( A ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ) ∧ B =   
 \<cpnf> ) ⟶ ( B \<ls> C ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_adantll)
   from S12 have S13: "( ( A ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ) ∧ B =   
 \<cpnf> ) ⟶ ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_adantld)
   have S14: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ A ∈ ℝ⇧*" by (rule MMI_rexrt)
   have S15: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_nltmnft)
   from S14 S15 have S16: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S16 have S17: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   have S18: "B = \<cmnf> ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟷ A \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_breq2)
   from S18 have S19: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟷ A \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S17 S19 have S20: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> B )" by (rule MMI_mtbird)
   from S20 have S21: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_pm2_21d)
   from S21 have S22: "( ( A ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ) ∧ B =   
 \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_adantlr)
   from S22 have S23: "( ( A ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ) ∧ B =   
 \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_adantrd)
   from S3 S13 S23 have S24: "( ( A ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ) ∧ ( B ∈ ℝ ∨ B = \<cpnf> ∨ B = \<cmnf> ) ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_3jaodan)
   have S25: "B ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟷ ( B ∈ ℝ ∨ B = \<cpnf> ∨ B = \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_elxr)
   from S24 S25 have S26: "( ( A ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ) ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_sylan2b)
   from S26 have S27: "( ( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ∧ C ∈ ℝ ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_an1rs)
   have S28: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ A \<ls> \<cpnf>" by (rule MMI_ltpnft)
   from S28 have S29: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ C = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ A \<ls> \<cpnf>" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   have S30: "C = \<cpnf> ⟶ ( A \<ls> C ⟷ A \<ls> \<cpnf> )" by (rule MMI_breq2)
   from S30 have S31: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ C = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> C ⟷ A \<ls> \<cpnf> )" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S29 S31 have S32: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ C = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ A \<ls> C" by (rule MMI_mpbird)
   from S32 have S33: "( ( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ∧ C = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ A \<ls> C" by (rule MMI_adantlr)
   from S33 have S34: "( ( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ∧ C =   
 \<cpnf> ) ⟶ ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_a1d)
   have S35: "B ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_nltmnft)
   from S35 have S36: "( B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   have S37: "C = \<cmnf> ⟶ ( B \<ls> C ⟷ B \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_breq2)
   from S37 have S38: "( B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ( B \<ls> C ⟷ B \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S36 S38 have S39: "( B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_mtbird)
   from S39 have S40: "( B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C = \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ( B \<ls> C ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_pm2_21d)
   from S40 have S41: "( B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C =   
 \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_adantld)
   from S41 have S42: "( ( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ∧ C =   
 \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_adantll)
   from S27 S34 S42 have S43: "( ( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℝ ∨ C = \<cpnf> ∨ C = \<cmnf> ) ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_3jaodan)
   from S43 have S44: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ ( B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ ( C ∈ ℝ ∨ C = \<cpnf> ∨ C = \<cmnf> ) ) ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_anasss)
   have S45: "B ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ¬ ( \<cpnf> \<ls> B )" by (rule MMI_pnfnltt)
   from S45 have S46: "( A = \<cpnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶ ¬ ( \<cpnf> \<ls> B )" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   have S47: "A = \<cpnf> ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟷ \<cpnf> \<ls> B )" 
     by (rule MMI_breq1)
   from S47 have S48: "( A = \<cpnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟷ \<cpnf> \<ls> B )" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   from S46 S48 have S49: "( A = \<cpnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> B )" 
     by (rule MMI_mtbird)
   from S49 have S50: "( A = \<cpnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟶ A \<ls> C )" 
     by (rule MMI_pm2_21d)
   from S50 have S51: "( A =   
 \<cpnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_adantrd)
   from S51 have S52: "( A =   
 \<cpnf> ∧ ( B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ ( C ∈ ℝ ∨ C = \<cpnf> ∨ C = \<cmnf> ) ) ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_adantrr)
   have S53: "C ∈ ℝ ⟶ \<cmnf> \<ls> C" by (rule MMI_mnfltt)
   from S53 have S54: "( A = \<cmnf> ∧ C ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ \<cmnf> \<ls> C" 
     by (rule MMI_adantl)
   have S55: "A = \<cmnf> ⟶ ( A \<ls> C ⟷ \<cmnf> \<ls> C )" 
     by (rule MMI_breq1)
   from S55 have S56: "( A = \<cmnf> ∧ C ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> C ⟷ \<cmnf> \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   from S54 S56 have S57: "( A = \<cmnf> ∧ C ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ A \<ls> C" 
     by (rule MMI_mpbird)
   from S57 have S58: "( A =   
 \<cmnf> ∧ C ∈ ℝ ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_a1d)
   from S58 have S59: "( ( A = \<cmnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ∧ C ∈ ℝ ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_adantlr)
   have S60: "\<cmnf> \<ls> \<cpnf>" by (rule MMI_mnfltpnf)
   have S61: 
     "( A = \<cmnf> ∧ C = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> C ⟷ \<cmnf> \<ls> \<cpnf> )" 
     by (rule MMI_breq12)
   from S60 S61 have S62: "( A = \<cmnf> ∧ C = \<cpnf> ) ⟶ A \<ls> C" 
     by (rule MMI_mpbiri)
   from S62 have S63: "( A =   
 \<cmnf> ∧ C =   
 \<cpnf> ) ⟶ ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_a1d)
   from S63 have S64: "( ( A = \<cmnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ∧ C =   
 \<cpnf> ) ⟶ ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_adantlr)
   from S41 have S65: "( B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C =   
 \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" .
   from S65 have S66: "( ( A = \<cmnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ∧ C =   
 \<cmnf> ) ⟶ ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_adantll)
   from S59 S64 S66 have S67: 
     "( ( A = \<cmnf> ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ∧ ( C ∈ ℝ ∨ C = \<cpnf> ∨ C = \<cmnf> ) ) ⟶ 
      ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_3jaodan)
   from S67 have S68: "( A =   
 \<cmnf> ∧ ( B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ ( C ∈ ℝ ∨ C = \<cpnf> ∨ C = \<cmnf> ) ) ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_anasss)
   from S44 S52 S68 have S69: "( ( A ∈ ℝ ∨ A = \<cpnf> ∨ A = \<cmnf> ) ∧ ( B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ ( C ∈ ℝ ∨ C = \<cpnf> ∨ C = \<cmnf> ) ) ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_3jaoian)
   from S69 have S70: "( ( A ∈ ℝ ∨ A = \<cpnf> ∨ A = \<cmnf> ) ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ ( C ∈ ℝ ∨ C = \<cpnf> ∨ C = \<cmnf> ) ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_3impb)
   have S71: "C ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟷ ( C ∈ ℝ ∨ C = \<cpnf> ∨ C = \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_elxr)
   from S70 S71 have S72: "( ( A ∈ ℝ ∨ A = \<cpnf> ∨ A = \<cmnf> ) ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_syl3an3b)
   have S73: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟷ ( A ∈ ℝ ∨ A = \<cpnf> ∨ A = \<cmnf> )" 
     by (rule MMI_elxr)
   from S72 S73 show "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_syl3an1b)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_xrltso: 
   shows "\<cltrrset> Orders ℝ⇧*"
proof -
  { fix x y z
    have S1: "( x ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ y ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
      ( x \<ls> y ⟷ ¬ ( ( x = y ∨ y \<ls> x ) ) )" by (rule MMI_xrlttrit)
    from S1 have S2: "( x ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ y ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ z ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
      ( x \<ls> y ⟷ ¬ ( ( x = y ∨ y \<ls> x ) ) )" by (rule MMI_3adant3)
    have S3: "( x ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ y ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ z ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
      ( ( x \<ls> y ∧ y \<ls> z ) ⟶ x \<ls> z )" by (rule MMI_xrlttrt)
    from S2 S3 have S4: 
      "( x ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ y ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ z ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   ( ( x \<ls> y ⟷ 
      ¬ ( ( x = y ∨ y \<ls> x ) ) ) ∧ ( ( x \<ls> y ∧ y \<ls> z ) ⟶ 
      x \<ls> z ) )" by (rule MMI_jca)
    then have  "x ∈ ℝ⇧*  ∧ y ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ z ∈ ℝ⇧*  ⟶   
      ( ( ⟨x,y⟩ ∈ \<cltrrset> ⟷ ¬ ( ( x = y ∨ ⟨y, x⟩ ∈ \<cltrrset> ) ) ) ∧ 
      ( ( ⟨x, y⟩ ∈ \<cltrrset>  ∧ ⟨y, z⟩ ∈ \<cltrrset> ) ⟶ 
      ⟨x, z⟩ ∈ \<cltrrset> ) )"
      using cltrr_def by simp
  } then have "∀x y z. ( x ∈ ℝ⇧*  ∧ y ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ z ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
      ( ( ⟨x,y⟩ ∈ \<cltrrset> ⟷ ¬ ( ( x = y ∨ ⟨y, x⟩ ∈ \<cltrrset> ) ) ) ∧ 
      ( ( ⟨x, y⟩ ∈ \<cltrrset>  ∧ ⟨y, z⟩ ∈ \<cltrrset> ) ⟶ 
      ⟨x, z⟩ ∈ \<cltrrset> ) )" by auto
  thus "\<cltrrset> Orders ℝ⇧*" by (rule MMI_so)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_xrlttri3t: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
  ( A = B ⟷ ( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ∧ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "\<cltrrset> Orders ℝ⇧*" by (rule MMI_xrltso)
   have "( \<cltrrset> Orders ℝ⇧* ∧ ( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ) ⟶   
     ( A = B ⟷ ( ¬ ( ⟨A,B⟩ ∈ \<cltrrset>  ) ∧ ¬ ( ⟨B, A⟩ ∈ \<cltrrset> ) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_sotrieq2)
   then have S2: "( \<cltrrset> Orders ℝ⇧* ∧ ( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ) ⟶   
     ( A = B ⟷ ( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ∧ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) ) )" 
     using cltrr_def by simp
   from S1 S2 show "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
     ( A =   
     B ⟷ ( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ∧ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) ) )" by (rule MMI_mpan)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_xrleloet: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
  ( A \<lsq> B ⟷ ( A \<ls> B ∨ A = B ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A \<lsq> B ⟷ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_xrlenltt)
   have S2: "( B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ A ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( B \<ls> A ⟷ ¬ ( ( B = A ∨ A \<ls> B ) ) )" by (rule MMI_xrlttrit)
   from S2 have S3: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( B \<ls> A ⟷ ¬ ( ( B = A ∨ A \<ls> B ) ) )" by (rule MMI_ancoms)
   from S3 have S4: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( B = A ∨ A \<ls> B ) ⟷ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_con2bid)
   have S5: "B = A ⟷ A = B" by (rule MMI_eqcom)
   from S5 have S6: "( B = A ∨ A \<ls> B ) ⟷ ( A = B ∨ A \<ls> B )" by (rule MMI_orbi1i)
   have S7: "( A = B ∨ A \<ls> B ) ⟷ ( A \<ls> B ∨ A = B )" by (rule MMI_orcom)
   from S6 S7 have S8: "( B = A ∨ A \<ls> B ) ⟷ ( A \<ls> B ∨ A = B )" by (rule MMI_bitr)
   from S4 S8 have S9: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) ⟷ ( A \<ls> B ∨ A = B ) )" by (rule MMI_syl5rbbr)
   from S1 S9 show "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A \<lsq> B ⟷ ( A \<ls> B ∨ A = B ) )" by (rule MMI_bitrd)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_xrleltnet: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ A \<lsq> B ) ⟶   
 ( A \<ls> B ⟷ ¬ ( A = B ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A =   
 B ⟷ ( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ∧ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) ) )" by (rule MMI_xrlttri3t)
   have S2: "( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ∧ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) ) ⟶   
 ¬ ( A \<ls> B )" by (rule MMI_pm3_26)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A = B ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) )" by (rule MMI_syl6bi)
   from S3 have S4: "( ( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ∧ A \<lsq> B ) ⟶   
 ( A = B ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) )" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   have S5: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A \<lsq> B ⟷ ( A \<ls> B ∨ A = B ) )" by (rule MMI_xrleloet)
   from S5 have S6: "( ( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ∧ A \<lsq> B ) ⟶   
 ( A \<ls> B ∨ A = B )" by (rule MMI_biimpa)
   from S6 have S7: "( ( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ∧ A \<lsq> B ) ⟶   
 ( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ⟶ A = B )" by (rule MMI_ord)
   from S4 S7 have S8: "( ( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ∧ A \<lsq> B ) ⟶   
 ( A = B ⟷ ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) )" by (rule MMI_impbid)
   from S8 have S9: "( ( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ∧ A \<lsq> B ) ⟶   
 ( A \<ls> B ⟷ ¬ ( A = B ) )" by (rule MMI_con2bid)
   from S9 show "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ A \<lsq> B ) ⟶   
 ( A \<ls> B ⟷ ¬ ( A = B ) )" by (rule MMI_3impa)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_xrltlet: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟶ A \<lsq> B )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A \<lsq> B ⟷ ( A \<ls> B ∨ A = B ) )" by (rule MMI_xrleloet)
   have S2: "A \<ls> B ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ∨ A = B )" by (rule MMI_orc)
   from S1 S2 show "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟶ A \<lsq> B )" by (rule MMI_syl5bir)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_xrlelttrt: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<lsq> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )"
proof -
   have S1: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A \<lsq> B ⟷ ( A \<ls> B ∨ A = B ) )" by (rule MMI_xrleloet)
   from S1 have S2: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A \<lsq> B ⟷ ( A \<ls> B ∨ A = B ) )" by (rule MMI_3adant3)
   have S3: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_xrlttrt)
   from S3 have S4: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A \<ls> B ⟶ ( B \<ls> C ⟶ A \<ls> C ) )" by (rule MMI_exp3a)
   have S5: "A = B ⟶ ( A \<ls> C ⟷ B \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_breq1)
   from S5 have S6: "A = B ⟶ ( B \<ls> C ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_biimprd)
   from S6 have S7: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A = B ⟶ ( B \<ls> C ⟶ A \<ls> C ) )" by (rule MMI_a1i)
   from S4 S7 have S8: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∨ A = B ) ⟶   
 ( B \<ls> C ⟶ A \<ls> C ) )" by (rule MMI_jaod)
   from S2 S8 have S9: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A \<lsq> B ⟶ ( B \<ls> C ⟶ A \<ls> C ) )" by (rule MMI_sylbid)
   from S9 show "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<lsq> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_imp3a)
qed

(**************** 281-290 ***********************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_xrltletrt: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<lsq> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )"
proof -
   have S1: "( B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( B \<lsq> C ⟷ ( B \<ls> C ∨ B = C ) )" by (rule MMI_xrleloet)
   from S1 have S2: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( B \<lsq> C ⟷ ( B \<ls> C ∨ B = C ) )" by (rule MMI_3adant1)
   have S3: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_xrlttrt)
   from S3 have S4: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A \<ls> B ⟶ ( B \<ls> C ⟶ A \<ls> C ) )" by (rule MMI_exp3a)
   from S4 have S5: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( B \<ls> C ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟶ A \<ls> C ) )" by (rule MMI_com23)
   have S6: "B = C ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟷ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_breq2)
   from S6 have S7: "B = C ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_biimpd)
   from S7 have S8: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( B = C ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟶ A \<ls> C ) )" by (rule MMI_a1i)
   from S5 S8 have S9: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( B \<ls> C ∨ B = C ) ⟶   
 ( A \<ls> B ⟶ A \<ls> C ) )" by (rule MMI_jaod)
   from S2 S9 have S10: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( B \<lsq> C ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟶ A \<ls> C ) )" by (rule MMI_sylbid)
   from S10 have S11: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A \<ls> B ⟶ ( B \<lsq> C ⟶ A \<ls> C ) )" by (rule MMI_com23)
   from S11 show "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∧ B \<lsq> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_imp3a)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_xrletrt: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<lsq> B ∧ B \<lsq> C ) ⟶ A \<lsq> C )"
proof -
   have S1: "( B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( B \<lsq> C ⟷ ( B \<ls> C ∨ B = C ) )" by (rule MMI_xrleloet)
   from S1 have S2: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( B \<lsq> C ⟷ ( B \<ls> C ∨ B = C ) )" by (rule MMI_3adant1)
   from S2 have S3: "( ( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ∧ A \<lsq> B ) ⟶   
 ( B \<lsq> C ⟷ ( B \<ls> C ∨ B = C ) )" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   have S4: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<lsq> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<ls> C )" by (rule MMI_xrlelttrt)
   have S5: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> C ⟶ A \<lsq> C )" 
     by (rule MMI_xrltlet)
   from S5 have S6: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A \<ls> C ⟶ A \<lsq> C )" by (rule MMI_3adant2)
   from S4 S6 have S7: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<lsq> B ∧ B \<ls> C ) ⟶ A \<lsq> C )" by (rule MMI_syld)
   from S7 have S8: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A \<lsq> B ⟶ ( B \<ls> C ⟶ A \<lsq> C ) )" by (rule MMI_exp3a)
   from S8 have S9: "( ( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ∧ A \<lsq> B ) ⟶   
 ( B \<ls> C ⟶ A \<lsq> C )" by (rule MMI_imp)
   have S10: "B = C ⟶ ( A \<lsq> B ⟷ A \<lsq> C )" by (rule MMI_breq2)
   from S10 have S11: "A \<lsq> B ⟶ ( B = C ⟶ A \<lsq> C )" 
     by (rule MMI_biimpcd)
   from S11 have S12: "( ( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ∧ A \<lsq> B ) ⟶   
 ( B = C ⟶ A \<lsq> C )" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S9 S12 have S13: "( ( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ∧ A \<lsq> B ) ⟶   
 ( ( B \<ls> C ∨ B = C ) ⟶ A \<lsq> C )" by (rule MMI_jaod)
   from S3 S13 have S14: "( ( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ∧ A \<lsq> B ) ⟶   
 ( B \<lsq> C ⟶ A \<lsq> C )" by (rule MMI_sylbid)
   from S14 have S15: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A \<lsq> B ⟶ ( B \<lsq> C ⟶ A \<lsq> C ) )" by (rule MMI_ex)
   from S15 show "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ C ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<lsq> B ∧ B \<lsq> C ) ⟶ A \<lsq> C )" by (rule MMI_imp3a)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_xrltnet: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A \<ls> B ⟶ ¬ ( A = B ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "\<cltrrset> Orders ℝ⇧*" by (rule MMI_xrltso)
   have  "( \<cltrrset> Orders ℝ⇧* ∧ ( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ) ⟶   
     ( A = B ⟷ ¬ ( ( ⟨A, B⟩ ∈ \<cltrrset> ∨ ⟨B,A⟩ ∈ \<cltrrset> ) ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_sotrieq)
   then have S2: "( \<cltrrset> Orders ℝ⇧* ∧ ( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ) ⟶   
     ( A = B ⟷ ¬ ( ( A \<ls> B ∨ B \<ls> A ) ) )" 
     using cltrr_def by simp
   from S1 S2 have S3: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
     ( A = B ⟷ ¬ ( ( A \<ls> B ∨ B \<ls> A ) ) )" by (rule MMI_mpan)
   from S3 have S4: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<ls> B ∨ B \<ls> A ) ⟷ ¬ ( A = B ) )" by (rule MMI_con2bid)
   have S5: "A \<ls> B ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ∨ B \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_orc)
   from S4 S5 show "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A \<ls> B ⟶ ¬ ( A = B ) )" by (rule MMI_syl5bi)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_nltpnftt: 
   shows "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( A = \<cpnf> ⟷ ¬ ( A \<ls> \<cpnf> ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "\<cpnf> ∈ ℝ⇧*" by (rule MMI_pnfxr)
   have S2: "\<cpnf> ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ¬ ( \<cpnf> \<ls> \<cpnf> )" by (rule MMI_xrltnrt)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "¬ ( \<cpnf> \<ls> \<cpnf> )" by (rule MMI_ax_mp)
   have S4: "A = \<cpnf> ⟶ ( A \<ls> \<cpnf> ⟷ \<cpnf> \<ls> \<cpnf> )" by (rule MMI_breq1)
   from S3 S4 have S5: "A = \<cpnf> ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> \<cpnf> )" by (rule MMI_mtbiri)
   from S5 have S6: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( A = \<cpnf> ⟶ ¬ ( A \<ls> \<cpnf> ) )" by (rule MMI_a1i)
   have S7: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ A \<lsq> \<cpnf>" by (rule MMI_pnfget)
   have S8: "\<cpnf> ∈ ℝ⇧*" by (rule MMI_pnfxr)
   have S9: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ \<cpnf> ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( A \<lsq> \<cpnf> ⟷ ( A \<ls> \<cpnf> ∨ A = \<cpnf> ) )" by (rule MMI_xrleloet)
   from S8 S9 have S10: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( A \<lsq> \<cpnf> ⟷ ( A \<ls> \<cpnf> ∨ A = \<cpnf> ) )" by (rule MMI_mpan2)
   from S7 S10 have S11: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( A \<ls> \<cpnf> ∨ A = \<cpnf> )" by (rule MMI_mpbid)
   from S11 have S12: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( ¬ ( A \<ls> \<cpnf> ) ⟶ A = \<cpnf> )" by (rule MMI_ord)
   from S6 S12 show "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( A = \<cpnf> ⟷ ¬ ( A \<ls> \<cpnf> ) )" by (rule MMI_impbid)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_ngtmnftt: 
   shows "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( A = \<cmnf> ⟷ ¬ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "\<cmnf> ∈ ℝ⇧*" by (rule MMI_mnfxr)
   have S2: "\<cmnf> ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ¬ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_xrltnrt)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "¬ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_ax_mp)
   have S4: "A = \<cmnf> ⟶ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ⟷ \<cmnf> \<ls> \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_breq2)
   from S3 S4 have S5: "A = \<cmnf> ⟶ ¬ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_mtbiri)
   from S5 have S6: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( A = \<cmnf> ⟶ ¬ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_a1i)
   have S7: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ \<cmnf> \<lsq> A" by (rule MMI_mnflet)
   have S8: "\<cmnf> ∈ ℝ⇧*" by (rule MMI_mnfxr)
   have S9: "( \<cmnf> ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ A ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( \<cmnf> \<lsq> A ⟷ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ∨ \<cmnf> = A ) )" by (rule MMI_xrleloet)
   from S8 S9 have S10: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( \<cmnf> \<lsq> A ⟷ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ∨ \<cmnf> = A ) )" by (rule MMI_mpan)
   from S7 S10 have S11: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ∨ \<cmnf> = A )" by (rule MMI_mpbid)
   from S11 have S12: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( ¬ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ) ⟶ \<cmnf> = A )" by (rule MMI_ord)
   have S13: "\<cmnf> = A ⟷ A = \<cmnf>" by (rule MMI_eqcom)
   from S12 S13 have S14: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( ¬ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ) ⟶ A = \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_syl6ib)
   from S6 S14 show "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( A = \<cmnf> ⟷ ¬ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_impbid)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_xrrebndt: 
   shows "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( A ∈ ℝ ⟷ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ∧ A \<ls> \<cpnf> ) )"
proof -
   have S1: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ \<cmnf> \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_mnfltt)
   have S2: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ A \<ls> \<cpnf>" by (rule MMI_ltpnft)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ∧ A \<ls> \<cpnf> )" 
     by (rule MMI_jca)
   from S3 have S4: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( A ∈ ℝ ⟶ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ∧ A \<ls> \<cpnf> ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_a1i)
   have S5: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( A = \<cpnf> ⟷ ¬ ( A \<ls> \<cpnf> ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_nltpnftt)
   have S6: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( A = \<cmnf> ⟷ ¬ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_ngtmnftt)
   from S5 S6 have S7: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶   
     ( ( A = \<cpnf> ∨ A = \<cmnf> ) ⟷   
     ( ¬ ( A \<ls> \<cpnf>) ∨ ¬ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ) ) )" by (rule MMI_orbi12d)
   have S8: "¬ ( ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ∧ A \<ls> \<cpnf> ) ) ⟷   
     ( ¬ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ) ∨ ¬ ( A \<ls> \<cpnf> ) )" by (rule MMI_ianor)
   have S9: "( ¬ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ) ∨ ¬ ( A \<ls> \<cpnf> ) ) ⟷   
     ( ¬ ( A \<ls> \<cpnf> ) ∨ ¬ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_orcom)
   from S8 S9 have S10: "( ¬ ( A \<ls> \<cpnf> ) ∨ ¬ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ) ) ⟷   
     ¬ ( ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ) ∧ A \<ls> \<cpnf> )" by (rule MMI_bitr2)
   from S7 S10 have S11: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶   
 ( ( A = \<cpnf> ∨ A = \<cmnf> ) ⟷   
 ¬ ( ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ∧ A \<ls> \<cpnf> ) ) )" by (rule MMI_syl6bb)
   from S11 have S12: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶   
 ( ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ∧ A \<ls> \<cpnf> ) ⟷   
 ¬ ( ( A = \<cpnf> ∨ A = \<cmnf> ) ) )" by (rule MMI_con2bid)
   have S13: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟷ ( A ∈ ℝ ∨ A = \<cpnf> ∨ A = \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_elxr)
   from S13 have S14: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( A ∈ ℝ ∨ A = \<cpnf> ∨ A = \<cmnf> )" by (rule MMI_biimp)
   have S15: "( A ∈ ℝ ∨ A =   
 \<cpnf> ∨ A =   
 \<cmnf> ) ⟷ ( A ∈ ℝ ∨ ( A = \<cpnf> ∨ A = \<cmnf> ) )" by (rule MMI_3orass)
   have S16: "( A ∈ ℝ ∨ ( A = \<cpnf> ∨ A = \<cmnf> ) ) ⟷   
 ( ( A = \<cpnf> ∨ A = \<cmnf> ) ∨ A ∈ ℝ )" by (rule MMI_orcom)
   from S15 S16 have S17: "( A ∈ ℝ ∨ A =   
 \<cpnf> ∨ A =   
 \<cmnf> ) ⟷ ( ( A = \<cpnf> ∨ A = \<cmnf> ) ∨ A ∈ ℝ )" by (rule MMI_bitr)
   from S14 S17 have S18: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( ( A = \<cpnf> ∨ A = \<cmnf> ) ∨ A ∈ ℝ )" by (rule MMI_sylib)
   from S18 have S19: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶   
 ( ¬ ( ( A = \<cpnf> ∨ A = \<cmnf> ) ) ⟶ A ∈ ℝ )" by (rule MMI_ord)
   from S12 S19 have S20: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ∧ A \<ls> \<cpnf> ) ⟶ A ∈ ℝ )" by (rule MMI_sylbid)
   from S4 S20 show "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( A ∈ ℝ ⟷ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ∧ A \<ls> \<cpnf> ) )" by (rule MMI_impbid)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_xrret: 
   shows "( ( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ∧ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ∧ A \<lsq> B ) ) ⟶   
 A ∈ ℝ"
proof -
   have S1: "( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ∧ A \<lsq> B ) ⟶ \<cmnf> \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_pm3_26)
   from S1 have S2: "( ( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ∧ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ∧ A \<lsq> B ) ) ⟶   
 \<cmnf> \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   have S3: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ B \<ls> \<cpnf>" by (rule MMI_ltpnft)
   from S3 have S4: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ B \<ls> \<cpnf>" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   have S5: "\<cpnf> ∈ ℝ⇧*" by (rule MMI_pnfxr)
   have S6: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ \<cpnf> ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<lsq> B ∧ B \<ls> \<cpnf> ) ⟶ A \<ls> \<cpnf> )" by (rule MMI_xrlelttrt)
   from S5 S6 have S7: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ⇧* ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<lsq> B ∧ B \<ls> \<cpnf> ) ⟶ A \<ls> \<cpnf> )" by (rule MMI_mp3an3)
   have S8: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ B ∈ ℝ⇧*" by (rule MMI_rexrt)
   from S7 S8 have S9: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶   
 ( ( A \<lsq> B ∧ B \<ls> \<cpnf> ) ⟶ A \<ls> \<cpnf> )" by (rule MMI_sylan2)
   from S4 S9 have S10: "( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ ( A \<lsq> B ⟶ A \<ls> \<cpnf> )" by (rule MMI_mpan2d)
   from S10 have S11: "( ( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ∧ A \<lsq> B ) ⟶ A \<ls> \<cpnf>" by (rule MMI_imp)
   from S11 have S12: "( ( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ∧ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ∧ A \<lsq> B ) ) ⟶   
 A \<ls> \<cpnf>" by (rule MMI_adantrl)
   from S2 S12 have S13: "( ( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ∧ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ∧ A \<lsq> B ) ) ⟶   
 ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ∧ A \<ls> \<cpnf> )" by (rule MMI_jca)
   have S14: "A ∈ ℝ⇧* ⟶ ( A ∈ ℝ ⟷ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ∧ A \<ls> \<cpnf> ) )" by (rule MMI_xrrebndt)
   from S14 have S15: "( ( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ∧ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ∧ A \<lsq> B ) ) ⟶   
 ( A ∈ ℝ ⟷ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ∧ A \<ls> \<cpnf> ) )" by (rule MMI_ad2antrr)
   from S13 S15 show "( ( A ∈ ℝ⇧* ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ∧ ( \<cmnf> \<ls> A ∧ A \<lsq> B ) ) ⟶   
 A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_mpbird)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_eqlet: 
   shows "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ A = B ) ⟶ A \<lsq> B"
proof -
   have S1: "A = B ⟶ ( A \<lsq> A ⟷ A \<lsq> B )" by (rule MMI_breq2)
   from S1 have S2: "( A \<lsq> A ∧ A = B ) ⟶ A \<lsq> B" by (rule MMI_biimpac)
   have S3: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ A \<lsq> A" by (rule MMI_leidt)
   from S2 S3 show "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ A = B ) ⟶ A \<lsq> B" by (rule MMI_sylan)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_lttri2: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "¬ ( A = B ) ⟷ ( A \<ls> B ∨ B \<ls> A )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   have S3: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶   
 ( ¬ ( A = B ) ⟷ ( A \<ls> B ∨ B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_lttri2t)
   from S1 S2 S3 show "¬ ( A = B ) ⟷ ( A \<ls> B ∨ B \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_mp2an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_lttri3: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A = B ⟷ ( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ∧ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   have S3: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶   
 ( A = B ⟷ ( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ∧ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) ) )" by (rule MMI_lttri3t)
   from S1 S2 S3 show "A = B ⟷ ( ¬ ( A \<ls> B ) ∧ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) )" 
     by (rule MMI_mp2an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_letri3: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A = B ⟷ ( A \<lsq> B ∧ B \<lsq> A )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   have S3: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶   
 ( A = B ⟷ ( A \<lsq> B ∧ B \<lsq> A ) )" by (rule MMI_letri3t)
   from S1 S2 S3 show "A = B ⟷ ( A \<lsq> B ∧ B \<lsq> A )" by (rule MMI_mp2an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_leloe: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A \<lsq> B ⟷ ( A \<ls> B ∨ A = B )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   have S3: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶   
 ( A \<lsq> B ⟷ ( A \<ls> B ∨ A = B ) )" by (rule MMI_leloet)
   from S1 S2 S3 show "A \<lsq> B ⟷ ( A \<ls> B ∨ A = B )" by (rule MMI_mp2an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_ltlen: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A \<ls> B ⟷ ( A \<lsq> B ∧ ¬ ( A = B ) )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   have S3: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶   
 ( A \<ls> B ⟷ ( A \<lsq> B ∧ ¬ ( A = B ) ) )" by (rule MMI_ltlent)
   from S1 S2 S3 show "A \<ls> B ⟷ ( A \<lsq> B ∧ ¬ ( A = B ) )" by (rule MMI_mp2an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_ltnsym: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A \<ls> B ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> A )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   have S3: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶   
 ( A \<ls> B ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_ltnsymt)
   from S1 S2 S3 show "A \<ls> B ⟶ ¬ ( B \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_mp2an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_lenlt: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A \<lsq> B ⟷ ¬ ( B \<ls> A )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   have S3: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶   
 ( A \<lsq> B ⟷ ¬ ( B \<ls> A ) )" by (rule MMI_lenltt)
   from S1 S2 S3 show "A \<lsq> B ⟷ ¬ ( B \<ls> A )" by (rule MMI_mp2an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_ltnle: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A \<ls> B ⟷ ¬ ( B \<lsq> A )"
proof -
   from A2 have S1: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from A1 have S2: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "B \<lsq> A ⟷ ¬ ( A \<ls> B )" by (rule MMI_lenlt)
   from S3 show "A \<ls> B ⟷ ¬ ( B \<lsq> A )" by (rule MMI_con2bii)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_ltle: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A \<ls> B ⟶ A \<lsq> B"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   have S3: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶ ( A \<ls> B ⟶ A \<lsq> B )" 
     by (rule MMI_ltlet)
   from S1 S2 S3 show "A \<ls> B ⟶ A \<lsq> B" by (rule MMI_mp2an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_ltlei: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ" and
    A3: "A \<ls> B"   
   shows "A \<lsq> B"
proof -
   from A3 have S1: "A \<ls> B".
   from A1 have S2: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S3: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S2 S3 have S4: "A \<ls> B ⟶ A \<lsq> B" by (rule MMI_ltle)
   from S1 S4 show "A \<lsq> B" by (rule MMI_ax_mp)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_eqle: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A = B ⟶ A \<lsq> B"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "A = B ⟷ ( A \<lsq> B ∧ B \<lsq> A )" 
     by (rule MMI_letri3)
   from S3 show "A = B ⟶ A \<lsq> B" by (rule MMI_pm3_26bd)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_ltne: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A \<ls> B ⟶ ¬ ( A = B )"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   have S3: "( A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ) ⟶   
 ( A \<ls> B ⟶ ¬ ( A = B ) )" by (rule MMI_ltnet)
   from S1 S2 S3 show "A \<ls> B ⟶ ¬ ( A = B )" by (rule MMI_mp2an)
qed

(*********** 301, 302 ******************************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_letri: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A\<lsq>B ∨ B\<lsq>A"
proof -
   from A2 have S1: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from A1 have S2: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "B\<ls>A ⟷ ¬(A\<lsq>B)" by (rule MMI_ltnle)
   from A2 have S4: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from A1 have S5: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S4 S5 have S6: "B\<ls>A ⟶ B\<lsq>A" by (rule MMI_ltle)
   from S3 S6 have S7: "¬(A\<lsq>B) ⟶ B\<lsq>A" by (rule MMI_sylbir)
   from S7 show "A\<lsq>B ∨ B\<lsq>A" by (rule MMI_orri)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_lttr: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A\<ls>B ∧ B\<ls>C ⟶ A\<ls>C"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S3: "C ∈ ℝ".
   have S4: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ⟶ A\<ls>B ∧ B\<ls>C ⟶ A\<ls>C" by (rule MMI_axlttrn)
   from S1 S2 S3 S4 show "A\<ls>B ∧ B\<ls>C ⟶ A\<ls>C" by (rule MMI_mp3an)
qed

   from S1 S2 S3 S4 show "A\<lsq>B ∧ B\<ls>C ⟶ A\<ls>C" by (rule MMI_mp3an)

(********** 306 - 310 *************************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_le2tri3: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A\<lsq>B ∧ B\<lsq>C ∧ C\<lsq>A ⟷ A = B ∧ B = C ∧ C = A"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "A = B ⟷ A\<lsq>B ∧ B\<lsq>A" by (rule MMI_letri3)
   from S3 have S4: "A\<lsq>B ∧ B\<lsq>A ⟶ A = B" by (rule MMI_biimpr)
   from A2 have S5: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S6: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from A1 have S7: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S5 S6 S7 have S8: "B\<lsq>C ∧ C\<lsq>A ⟶ B\<lsq>A" by (rule MMI_letr)
   from S4 S8 have S9: "A\<lsq>B ∧ B\<lsq>C ∧ C\<lsq>A ⟶ A = B" by (rule MMI_sylan2)
   from S9 have S10: "A\<lsq>B ∧ B\<lsq>C ∧ C\<lsq>A ⟶ A = B" by (rule MMI_3impb)
   from A2 have S11: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S12: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S11 S12 have S13: "B = C ⟷ B\<lsq>C ∧ C\<lsq>B" by (rule MMI_letri3)
   from S13 have S14: "B\<lsq>C ∧ C\<lsq>B ⟶ B = C" by (rule MMI_biimpr)
   from A3 have S15: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from A1 have S16: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S17: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S15 S16 S17 have S18: "C\<lsq>A ∧ A\<lsq>B ⟶ C\<lsq>B" by (rule MMI_letr)
   from S14 S18 have S19: "B\<lsq>C ∧ C\<lsq>A ∧ A\<lsq>B ⟶ B = C" by (rule MMI_sylan2)
   from S19 have S20: "B\<lsq>C ∧ C\<lsq>A ∧ A\<lsq>B ⟶ B = C" by (rule MMI_3impb)
   from S20 have S21: "A\<lsq>B ∧ B\<lsq>C ∧ C\<lsq>A ⟶ B = C" by (rule MMI_3comr)
   from A1 have S22: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S23: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S22 S23 have S24: "A = C ⟷ A\<lsq>C ∧ C\<lsq>A" by (rule MMI_letri3)
   from S24 have S25: "A\<lsq>C ∧ C\<lsq>A ⟶ A = C" by (rule MMI_biimpr)
   from S25 have S26: "A\<lsq>C ∧ C\<lsq>A ⟶ C = A" by (rule MMI_eqcomd)
   from A1 have S27: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S28: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S29: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S27 S28 S29 have S30: "A\<lsq>B ∧ B\<lsq>C ⟶ A\<lsq>C" by (rule MMI_letr)
   from S26 S30 have S31: "( A\<lsq>B ∧ B\<lsq>C ) ∧ C\<lsq>A ⟶ C = A" by (rule MMI_sylan)
   from S31 have S32: "A\<lsq>B ∧ B\<lsq>C ∧ C\<lsq>A ⟶ C = A" by (rule MMI_3impa)
   from S10 S21 S32 have S33: "A\<lsq>B ∧ B\<lsq>C ∧ C\<lsq>A ⟶ A = B ∧ B = C ∧ C = A" 
     by (rule MMI_3jca)
   from A1 have S34: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S35: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S34 S35 have S36: "A = B ⟶ A\<lsq>B" by (rule MMI_eqle)
   from A2 have S37: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S38: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S37 S38 have S39: "B = C ⟶ B\<lsq>C" by (rule MMI_eqle)
   from A3 have S40: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from A1 have S41: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S40 S41 have S42: "C = A ⟶ C\<lsq>A" by (rule MMI_eqle)
   from S36 S39 S42 have S43: "A = B ∧ B = C ∧ C = A ⟶ A\<lsq>B ∧ B\<lsq>C ∧ C\<lsq>A" 
     by (rule MMI_3anim123i)
   from S33 S43 show "A\<lsq>B ∧ B\<lsq>C ∧ C\<lsq>A ⟷ A = B ∧ B = C ∧ C = A" by (rule MMI_impbi)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_ltadd2: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A\<ls>B ⟷ C \<ca> A\<ls>C \<ca> B"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S3: "C ∈ ℝ".
   have S4: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ⟶ A\<ls>B ⟶ C \<ca> A\<ls>C \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_axltadd)
   from S1 S2 S3 S4 have S5: "A\<ls>B ⟶ C \<ca> A\<ls>C \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_mp3an)
   from A3 have S6: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from A1 have S7: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S6 S7 have S8: "C \<ca> A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_readdcl)
   from A3 have S9: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S10: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S9 S10 have S11: "C \<ca> B ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_readdcl)
   from A3 have S12: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S12 have S13: "(\<cn>C) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegcl)
   have S14: "C \<ca> A ∈ ℝ ∧ C \<ca> B ∈ ℝ ∧ ( (\<cn>C) ∈ ℝ) ⟶ 
   C \<ca> A\<ls>C \<ca> B ⟶ (\<cn>C) \<ca> (C \<ca> A) \<ls> (\<cn>C) \<ca> (C \<ca> B)" 
     by (rule MMI_axltadd)
   from S8 S11 S13 S14 have S15: 
     "C \<ca> A\<ls>C \<ca> B ⟶ (\<cn>C) \<ca> (C \<ca> A) \<ls>(\<cn>C) \<ca> (C \<ca> B)" 
     by (rule MMI_mp3an)
   from S13 have S16: "(\<cn>C) ∈ ℝ" .
   from S16 have S17: "(\<cn>C) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from A3 have S18: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S18 have S19: "C ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S17 S19 have S20: "(\<cn>C) \<ca> C = C \<ca> (\<cn>C)" by (rule MMI_addcom)
   from S19 have S21: "C ∈ ℂ" .
   from S21 have S22: "C \<ca> (\<cn>C) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_negid)
   from S20 S22 have S23: "(\<cn>C) \<ca> C = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_eqtr)
   from S23 have S24: "(\<cn>C) \<ca> C \<ca> A = 𝟬 \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_opreq1i)
   from S17 have S25: "(\<cn>C) ∈ ℂ" .
   from S19 have S26: "C ∈ ℂ" .
   from A1 have S27: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S27 have S28: "A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S25 S26 S28 have S29: "( (\<cn>C) \<ca> C ) \<ca> A = (\<cn>C) \<ca> (C \<ca> A)" 
     by (rule MMI_addass)
   from S28 have S30: "A ∈ ℂ" .
   from S30 have S31: "𝟬 \<ca> A = A" by (rule MMI_addid2)
   from S24 S29 S31 have S32: "(\<cn>C) \<ca> ( C  \<ca> A ) = A" by (rule MMI_3eqtr3)
   from S23 have S33: "(\<cn>C) \<ca> C = 𝟬" .
   from S33 have S34: "(\<cn>C) \<ca> C \<ca> B = 𝟬 \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_opreq1i)
   from S17 have S35: "(\<cn>C) ∈ ℂ" .
   from S19 have S36: "C ∈ ℂ" .
   from A2 have S37: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S37 have S38: "B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S35 S36 S38 have S39: "(\<cn>C) \<ca> C \<ca> B = (\<cn>C) \<ca> ( C  \<ca> B)" 
     by (rule MMI_addass)
   from S38 have S40: "B ∈ ℂ" .
   from S40 have S41: "𝟬 \<ca> B = B" by (rule MMI_addid2)
   from S34 S39 S41 have S42: "(\<cn>C) \<ca> ( C \<ca> B) = B" by (rule MMI_3eqtr3)
   from S15 S32 S42 have S43: "C \<ca> A\<ls>C \<ca> B ⟶ A\<ls>B" by (rule MMI_3brtr3g)
   from S5 S43 show "A\<ls>B ⟷ C \<ca> A\<ls>C \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_impbi)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_ltadd1: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A\<ls>B ⟷ A \<ca> C\<ls>B \<ca> C"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S3: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S1 S2 S3 have S4: "A\<ls>B ⟷ C \<ca> A\<ls>C \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_ltadd2)
   from A3 have S5: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S5 have S6: "C ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from A1 have S7: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S7 have S8: "A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S6 S8 have S9: "C \<ca> A = A \<ca> C" by (rule MMI_addcom)
   from S6 have S10: "C ∈ ℂ" .
   from A2 have S11: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S11 have S12: "B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S10 S12 have S13: "C \<ca> B = B \<ca> C" by (rule MMI_addcom)
   from S9 S13 have S14: "C \<ca> A\<ls>C \<ca> B ⟷ A \<ca> C\<ls>B \<ca> C" by (rule MMI_breq12i)
   from S4 S14 show "A\<ls>B ⟷ A \<ca> C\<ls>B \<ca> C" by (rule MMI_bitr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_leadd1: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A\<lsq>B ⟷ A \<ca> C\<lsq>B \<ca> C"
proof -
   from A2 have S1: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from A1 have S2: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S3: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S1 S2 S3 have S4: "B\<ls>A ⟷ B \<ca> C\<ls>A \<ca> C" by (rule MMI_ltadd1)
   from S4 have S5: "¬(B\<ls>A) ⟷ ¬(B \<ca> C\<ls>A \<ca> C)" by (rule MMI_negbii)
   from A1 have S6: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S7: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S6 S7 have S8: "A\<lsq>B ⟷ ¬(B\<ls>A)" by (rule MMI_lenlt)
   from A1 have S9: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S10: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S9 S10 have S11: "A \<ca> C ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_readdcl)
   from A2 have S12: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S13: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S12 S13 have S14: "B \<ca> C ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_readdcl)
   from S11 S14 have S15: "A \<ca> C\<lsq>B \<ca> C ⟷ ¬(B \<ca> C\<ls>A \<ca> C)" by (rule MMI_lenlt)
   from S5 S8 S15 show "A\<lsq>B ⟷ A \<ca> C\<lsq>B \<ca> C" by (rule MMI_3bitr4)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_leadd2: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A\<lsq>B ⟷ C \<ca> A\<lsq>C \<ca> B"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S3: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S1 S2 S3 have S4: "A\<lsq>B ⟷ A \<ca> C\<lsq>B \<ca> C" by (rule MMI_leadd1)
   from A1 have S5: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S5 have S6: "A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from A3 have S7: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S7 have S8: "C ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S6 S8 have S9: "A \<ca> C = C \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_addcom)
   from A2 have S10: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S10 have S11: "B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S8 have S12: "C ∈ ℂ" .
   from S11 S12 have S13: "B \<ca> C = C \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_addcom)
   from S9 S13 have S14: "A \<ca> C\<lsq>B \<ca> C ⟷ C \<ca> A\<lsq>C \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_breq12i)
   from S4 S14 show "A\<lsq>B ⟷ C \<ca> A\<lsq>C \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_bitr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_ltsubadd: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A \<cs> B\<ls>C ⟷ A\<ls>C \<ca> B"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S2 have S3: "(\<cn>B) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegcl)
   from S1 S3 have S4: "A \<ca> (\<cn>B) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_readdcl)
   from A3 have S5: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S6: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S4 S5 S6 have S7: "A \<ca> (\<cn>B)\<ls>C ⟷ 
   A \<ca> (\<cn>B) \<ca> B\<ls>C \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_ltadd1)
   from A1 have S8: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S8 have S9: "A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from A2 have S10: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S10 have S11: "B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S9 S11 have S12: "A \<ca> (\<cn>B) = A \<cs> B" by (rule MMI_negsub)
   from S12 have S13: "A \<ca> (\<cn>B)\<ls>C ⟷ A \<cs> B\<ls>C" by (rule MMI_breq1i)
   from S9 have S14: "A ∈ ℂ" .
   from S3 have S15: "(\<cn>B) ∈ ℝ" .
   from S15 have S16: "(\<cn>B) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S11 have S17: "B ∈ ℂ" .
   from S14 S16 S17 have S18: "A \<ca> (\<cn>B) \<ca> B = A \<ca> ((\<cn>B) \<ca> B)" by (rule MMI_addass)
   from S16 have S19: "(\<cn>B) ∈ ℂ" .
   from S11 have S20: "B ∈ ℂ" .
   from S19 S20 have S21: "(\<cn>B) \<ca> B = B \<ca> (\<cn>B)" by (rule MMI_addcom)
   from S11 have S22: "B ∈ ℂ" .
   from S22 have S23: "B \<ca> (\<cn>B) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_negid)
   from S21 S23 have S24: "(\<cn>B) \<ca> B = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_eqtr)
   from S24 have S25: "A \<ca> ((\<cn>B) \<ca> B) = A \<ca> 𝟬" by (rule MMI_opreq2i)
   from S9 have S26: "A ∈ ℂ" .
   from S26 have S27: "A \<ca> 𝟬 = A" by (rule MMI_addid1)
   from S18 S25 S27 have S28: "A \<ca> (\<cn>B) \<ca> B = A" by (rule MMI_3eqtr)
   from S28 have S29: "A \<ca> (\<cn>B) \<ca> B\<ls>C \<ca> B ⟷ A\<ls>C \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_breq1i)
   from S7 S13 S29 show "A \<cs> B\<ls>C ⟷ A\<ls>C \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_3bitr3)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_lesubadd: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A \<cs> B\<lsq>C ⟷ A\<lsq>C \<ca> B"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S3: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S1 S2 S3 have S4: "A \<cs> B\<ls>C ⟷ A\<ls>C \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_ltsubadd)
   from A1 have S5: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S5 have S6: "A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from A2 have S7: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S7 have S8: "B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from A3 have S9: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S9 have S10: "C ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S6 S8 S10 have S11: "A \<cs> B = C ⟷ B \<ca> C = A" by (rule MMI_subadd)
   from S8 have S12: "B ∈ ℂ" .
   from S10 have S13: "C ∈ ℂ" .
   from S12 S13 have S14: "B \<ca> C = C \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_addcom)
   from S14 have S15: "B \<ca> C = A ⟷ C \<ca> B = A" by (rule MMI_eqeq1i)
   have S16: "C \<ca> B = A ⟷ A = C \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_eqcom)
   from S11 S15 S16 have S17: "A \<cs> B = C ⟷ A = C \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_3bitr)
   from S4 S17 have S18: "A \<cs> B\<ls>C ∨ A \<cs> B = C ⟷ 
   A\<ls>C \<ca> B ∨ A = C \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_orbi12i_orig)
   from A1 have S19: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S20: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S19 S20 have S21: "A \<cs> B ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_resubcl)
   from A3 have S22: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S21 S22 have S23: "A \<cs> B\<lsq>C ⟷ 
   A \<cs> B\<ls>C ∨ A \<cs> B = C" by (rule MMI_leloe)
   from A1 have S24: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S25: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S26: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S25 S26 have S27: "C \<ca> B ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_readdcl)
   from S24 S27 have S28: "A\<lsq>C \<ca> B ⟷ 
   A\<ls>C \<ca> B ∨ A = C \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_leloe)
   from S18 S23 S28 show "A \<cs> B\<lsq>C ⟷ A\<lsq>C \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_3bitr4)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_lt2add: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℝ" and
    A4: "D ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A\<ls>C ∧ B\<ls>D ⟶ A \<ca> B\<ls>C \<ca> D"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "A \<ca> B ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_readdcl)
   from A3 have S4: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S5: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S4 S5 have S6: "C \<ca> B ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_readdcl)
   from A3 have S7: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from A4 have S8: "D ∈ ℝ".
   from S7 S8 have S9: "C \<ca> D ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_readdcl)
   from S3 S6 S9 have S10: "A \<ca> B\<ls>C \<ca> B ∧ C \<ca> B\<ls>C \<ca> D ⟶ A \<ca> B\<ls>C \<ca> D" by (rule MMI_lttr)
   from A1 have S11: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S12: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S13: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S11 S12 S13 have S14: "A\<ls>C ⟷ A \<ca> B\<ls>C \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_ltadd1)
   from A2 have S15: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from A4 have S16: "D ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S17: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S15 S16 S17 have S18: "B\<ls>D ⟷ C \<ca> B\<ls>C \<ca> D" by (rule MMI_ltadd2)
   from S10 S14 S18 show "A\<ls>C ∧ B\<ls>D ⟶ A \<ca> B\<ls>C \<ca> D" by (rule MMI_syl2anb)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_le2add: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℝ" and
    A4: "D ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A\<lsq>C ∧ B\<lsq>D ⟶ A \<ca> B\<lsq>C \<ca> D"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "A \<ca> B ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_readdcl)
   from A3 have S4: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S5: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S4 S5 have S6: "C \<ca> B ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_readdcl)
   from A3 have S7: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from A4 have S8: "D ∈ ℝ".
   from S7 S8 have S9: "C \<ca> D ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_readdcl)
   from S3 S6 S9 have S10: 
     "A \<ca> B\<lsq>C \<ca> B ∧ C \<ca> B\<lsq>C \<ca> D ⟶ 
     A \<ca> B\<lsq>C \<ca> D" by (rule MMI_letr)
   from A1 have S11: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S12: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S13: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S11 S12 S13 have S14: "A\<lsq>C ⟷ A \<ca> B\<lsq>C \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_leadd1)
   from A2 have S15: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from A4 have S16: "D ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S17: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S15 S16 S17 have S18: "B\<lsq>D ⟷ C \<ca> B\<lsq>C \<ca> D" by (rule MMI_leadd2)
   from S10 S14 S18 show "A\<lsq>C ∧ B\<lsq>D ⟶ A \<ca> B\<lsq>C \<ca> D" by (rule MMI_syl2anb)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_addgt0: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "𝟬\<ls>A ∧ 𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from A1 have S2: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A1 have S3: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S4: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S3 S4 have S5: "A \<ca> B ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_readdcl)
   from S1 S2 S5 have S6: "𝟬\<ls>A ∧ A\<ls>A \<ca> B ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_lttr)
   have S7: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from A2 have S8: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from A1 have S9: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S7 S8 S9 have S10: "𝟬\<ls>B ⟷ A \<ca> 𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_ltadd2)
   from A1 have S11: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S11 have S12: "A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S12 have S13: "A \<ca> 𝟬 = A" by (rule MMI_addid1)
   from S13 have S14: "A \<ca> 𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B ⟷ A\<ls>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_breq1i)
   from S10 S14 have S15: "𝟬\<ls>B ⟷ A\<ls>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_bitr)
   from S6 S15 show "𝟬\<ls>A ∧ 𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_sylan2b)
qed

(******* 316 - 320 *****************************************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_addge0: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "𝟬\<lsq>A ∧ 𝟬\<lsq>B ⟶ 𝟬\<lsq>A \<ca> B"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "𝟬\<ls>A ∧ 𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_addgt0)
   have S4: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from A1 have S5: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S6: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S5 S6 have S7: "A \<ca> B ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_readdcl)
   from S4 S7 have S8: "𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B ⟶ 𝟬\<lsq>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_ltle)
   from S3 S8 have S9: "𝟬\<ls>A ∧ 𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ 𝟬\<lsq>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_syl)
   have S10: "𝟬 = A ⟶ 𝟬 \<ca> B = A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   from A2 have S11: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S11 have S12: "B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S12 have S13: "𝟬 \<ca> B = B" by (rule MMI_addid2)
   from S10 S13 have S14: "𝟬 = A ⟶ B = A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_syl5eqr)
   from S14 have S15: "𝟬 = A ⟶ 
   𝟬\<ls>B ⟷ 𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_breq2d)
   from S15 have S16: "𝟬 = A ∧ 𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_biimpa)
   from S8 have S17: "𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B ⟶ 𝟬\<lsq>A \<ca> B" .
   from S16 S17 have S18: "𝟬 = A ∧ 𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ 𝟬\<lsq>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_syl)
   have S19: "𝟬 = B ⟶ A \<ca> 𝟬 = A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   from A1 have S20: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S20 have S21: "A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S21 have S22: "A \<ca> 𝟬 = A" by (rule MMI_addid1)
   from S19 S22 have S23: "𝟬 = B ⟶ A = A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_syl5eqr)
   from S23 have S24: "𝟬 = B ⟶ 
   𝟬\<ls>A ⟷ 𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_breq2d)
   from S24 have S25: "𝟬\<ls>A ∧ 𝟬 = B ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_biimpac)
   from S8 have S26: "𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B ⟶ 𝟬\<lsq>A \<ca> B" .
   from S25 S26 have S27: "𝟬\<ls>A ∧ 𝟬 = B ⟶ 𝟬\<lsq>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_syl)
   have S28: "𝟬 = A ∧ 𝟬 = B ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ca> 𝟬 = A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_opreq12)
   have S29: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S29 have S30: "𝟬 \<ca> 𝟬 = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_addid1)
   from S28 S30 have S31: "𝟬 = A ∧ 𝟬 = B ⟶ 𝟬 = A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_syl5eqr)
   have S32: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from S7 have S33: "A \<ca> B ∈ ℝ" .
   from S32 S33 have S34: "𝟬 = A \<ca> B ⟶ 𝟬\<lsq>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_eqle)
   from S31 S34 have S35: "𝟬 = A ∧ 𝟬 = B ⟶ 𝟬\<lsq>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S9 S18 S27 S35 have S36: "(𝟬\<ls>A ∨ 𝟬 = A) ∧ (𝟬\<ls>B ∨ 𝟬 = B) ⟶ 𝟬\<lsq>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_ccase)
   have S37: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from A1 have S38: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S37 S38 have S39: "𝟬\<lsq>A ⟷ 
   𝟬\<ls>A ∨ 𝟬 = A" by (rule MMI_leloe)
   have S40: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from A2 have S41: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S40 S41 have S42: "𝟬\<lsq>B ⟷ 
   𝟬\<ls>B ∨ 𝟬 = B" by (rule MMI_leloe)
   from S36 S39 S42 show "𝟬\<lsq>A ∧ 𝟬\<lsq>B ⟶ 𝟬\<lsq>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_syl2anb)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_addgegt0: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "𝟬\<lsq>A ∧ 𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from A1 have S2: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "𝟬\<lsq>A ⟷ 
   𝟬\<ls>A ∨ 𝟬 = A" by (rule MMI_leloe)
   from A1 have S4: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S5: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S4 S5 have S6: "𝟬\<ls>A ∧ 𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_addgt0)
   from S6 have S7: "𝟬\<ls>A ⟶ 
   𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_ex)
   have S8: "𝟬 = A ⟶ 𝟬 \<ca> B = A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   from A2 have S9: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S9 have S10: "B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S10 have S11: "𝟬 \<ca> B = B" by (rule MMI_addid2)
   from S8 S11 have S12: "𝟬 = A ⟶ B = A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_syl5eqr)
   from S12 have S13: "𝟬 = A ⟶ 
   𝟬\<ls>B ⟷ 𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_breq2d)
   from S13 have S14: "𝟬 = A ⟶ 
   𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_biimpd)
   from S7 S14 have S15: "𝟬\<ls>A ∨ 𝟬 = A ⟶ 
   𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_jaoi)
   from S3 S15 have S16: "𝟬\<lsq>A ⟶ 
   𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_sylbi)
   from S16 show "𝟬\<lsq>A ∧ 𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_imp)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_addgt0i: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ" and
    A3: "𝟬\<ls>A" and
    A4: "𝟬\<ls>B"   
   shows "𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B"
proof -
   from A3 have S1: "𝟬\<ls>A".
   from A4 have S2: "𝟬\<ls>B".
   from A1 have S3: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S4: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S3 S4 have S5: "𝟬\<ls>A ∧ 𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_addgt0)
   from S1 S2 S5 show "𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_mp2an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_add20: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "𝟬\<lsq>A ∧ 𝟬\<lsq>B ⟶ 
   A \<ca> B = 𝟬 ⟷ A = 𝟬 ∧ B = 𝟬"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "A \<ca> B ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_readdcl)
   have S4: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from S3 S4 have S5: "A \<ca> B = 𝟬 ⟷ 
   ¬(A \<ca> B\<ls>𝟬) ∧ ¬(𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B)" by (rule MMI_lttri3)
   from S5 have S6: "A \<ca> B = 𝟬 ⟶ ¬(𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B)" by (rule MMI_pm3_27bd)
   from A1 have S7: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S8: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S7 S8 have S9: "𝟬\<ls>A ∧ 𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_addgt0)
   from S6 S9 have S10: "𝟬\<ls>A ∧ 𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ ¬(A \<ca> B = 𝟬)" by (rule MMI_nsyl3)
   from S10 have S11: "𝟬\<ls>A ∧ 𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ 
   A \<ca> B = 𝟬 ⟶ A = 𝟬 ∧ B = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_pm2_21d)
   have S12: "𝟬 = A ⟶ 𝟬 \<ca> B = A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   from A2 have S13: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S13 have S14: "B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S14 have S15: "𝟬 \<ca> B = B" by (rule MMI_addid2)
   from S12 S15 have S16: "𝟬 = A ⟶ B = A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_syl5eqr)
   from S16 have S17: "𝟬 = A ⟶ 
   B = 𝟬 ⟷ A \<ca> B = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
   from S17 have S18: "𝟬 = A ⟶ 
   A \<ca> B = 𝟬 ⟶ B = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_biimprd)
   have S19: "𝟬 = A ⟷ A = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_eqcom)
   from S19 have S20: "𝟬 = A ⟶ A = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_biimp)
   from S18 S20 have S21: "𝟬 = A ⟶ 
   A \<ca> B = 𝟬 ⟶ A = 𝟬 ∧ B = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_jctild)
   have S22: "𝟬 = B ⟶ A \<ca> 𝟬 = A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   from A1 have S23: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S23 have S24: "A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S24 have S25: "A \<ca> 𝟬 = A" by (rule MMI_addid1)
   from S22 S25 have S26: "𝟬 = B ⟶ A = A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_syl5eqr)
   from S26 have S27: "𝟬 = B ⟶ 
   A = 𝟬 ⟷ A \<ca> B = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
   from S27 have S28: "𝟬 = B ⟶ 
   A \<ca> B = 𝟬 ⟶ A = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_biimprd)
   have S29: "𝟬 = B ⟷ B = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_eqcom)
   from S29 have S30: "𝟬 = B ⟶ B = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_biimp)
   from S28 S30 have S31: "𝟬 = B ⟶ 
   A \<ca> B = 𝟬 ⟶ A = 𝟬 ∧ B = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_jctird)
   from S11 S21 S31 have S32: "(𝟬\<ls>A ∨ 𝟬 = A) ∧ (𝟬\<ls>B ∨ 𝟬 = B) ⟶ 
   A \<ca> B = 𝟬 ⟶ A = 𝟬 ∧ B = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_ccase2)
   have S33: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from A1 have S34: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S33 S34 have S35: "𝟬\<lsq>A ⟷ 
   𝟬\<ls>A ∨ 𝟬 = A" by (rule MMI_leloe)
   have S36: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from A2 have S37: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S36 S37 have S38: "𝟬\<lsq>B ⟷ 
   𝟬\<ls>B ∨ 𝟬 = B" by (rule MMI_leloe)
   from S32 S35 S38 have S39: "𝟬\<lsq>A ∧ 𝟬\<lsq>B ⟶ 
   A \<ca> B = 𝟬 ⟶ A = 𝟬 ∧ B = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_syl2anb)
   have S40: "A = 𝟬 ⟶ A \<ca> B = 𝟬 \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   have S41: "B = 𝟬 ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ca> B = 𝟬 \<ca> 𝟬" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   have S42: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S42 have S43: "𝟬 \<ca> 𝟬 = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_addid1)
   from S41 S43 have S44: "B = 𝟬 ⟶ 𝟬 \<ca> B = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_syl6eq)
   from S40 S44 have S45: "A = 𝟬 ∧ B = 𝟬 ⟶ A \<ca> B = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_sylan9eq)
   from S45 have S46: "𝟬\<lsq>A ∧ 𝟬\<lsq>B ⟶ 
   A = 𝟬 ∧ B = 𝟬 ⟶ A \<ca> B = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_a1i)
   from S39 S46 show "𝟬\<lsq>A ∧ 𝟬\<lsq>B ⟶ 
   A \<ca> B = 𝟬 ⟷ A = 𝟬 ∧ B = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_impbid)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_ltneg: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A\<ls>B ⟷ (\<cn>B)\<ls>(\<cn>A)"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from A1 have S3: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S3 have S4: "(\<cn>A) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegcl)
   from A2 have S5: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S5 have S6: "(\<cn>B) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegcl)
   from S4 S6 have S7: "(\<cn>A) \<ca> (\<cn>B) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_readdcl)
   from S1 S2 S7 have S8: "A\<ls>B ⟷ 
   A \<ca> ((\<cn>A) \<ca> (\<cn>B))\<ls>B \<ca> ((\<cn>A) \<ca> (\<cn>B))" by (rule MMI_ltadd1)
   from A1 have S9: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S9 have S10: "A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S10 have S11: "A \<ca> (\<cn>A) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_negid)
   from S11 have S12: "A \<ca> (\<cn>A) \<ca> (\<cn>B) = 𝟬 \<ca> (\<cn>B)" by (rule MMI_opreq1i)
   from S10 have S13: "A ∈ ℂ" .
   from S4 have S14: "(\<cn>A) ∈ ℝ" .
   from S14 have S15: "(\<cn>A) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S6 have S16: "(\<cn>B) ∈ ℝ" .
   from S16 have S17: "(\<cn>B) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S13 S15 S17 have S18: "A \<ca> (\<cn>A) \<ca> (\<cn>B) = A \<ca> ((\<cn>A) \<ca> (\<cn>B))" by (rule MMI_addass)
   from S17 have S19: "(\<cn>B) ∈ ℂ" .
   from S19 have S20: "𝟬 \<ca> (\<cn>B) = (\<cn>B)" by (rule MMI_addid2)
   from S12 S18 S20 have S21: "A \<ca> ((\<cn>A) \<ca> (\<cn>B)) = (\<cn>B)" by (rule MMI_3eqtr3)
   from A2 have S22: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S22 have S23: "B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S15 have S24: "(\<cn>A) ∈ ℂ" .
   from S17 have S25: "(\<cn>B) ∈ ℂ" .
   from S23 S24 S25 have S26: "B \<ca> ((\<cn>A) \<ca> (\<cn>B)) = (\<cn>A) \<ca> (B \<ca> (\<cn>B))" by (rule MMI_add12)
   from S23 have S27: "B ∈ ℂ" .
   from S27 have S28: "B \<ca> (\<cn>B) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_negid)
   from S28 have S29: "(\<cn>A) \<ca> (B \<ca> (\<cn>B)) = (\<cn>A) \<ca> 𝟬" by (rule MMI_opreq2i)
   from S15 have S30: "(\<cn>A) ∈ ℂ" .
   from S30 have S31: "(\<cn>A) \<ca> 𝟬 = (\<cn>A)" by (rule MMI_addid1)
   from S26 S29 S31 have S32: "B \<ca> ((\<cn>A) \<ca> (\<cn>B)) = (\<cn>A)" by (rule MMI_3eqtr)
   from S21 S32 have S33: "A \<ca> ((\<cn>A) \<ca> (\<cn>B))\<ls>B \<ca> ((\<cn>A) \<ca> (\<cn>B)) ⟷ 
     (\<cn>B)\<ls>(\<cn>A)" by (rule MMI_breq12i)
   from S8 S33 show "A\<ls>B ⟷ (\<cn>B)\<ls>(\<cn>A)" by (rule MMI_bitr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_leneg: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A\<lsq>B ⟷ (\<cn>B)\<lsq>(\<cn>A)"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "A\<ls>B ⟷ (\<cn>B)\<ls>(\<cn>A)" by (rule MMI_ltneg)
   from A2 have S4: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S4 have S5: "B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from A1 have S6: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S6 have S7: "A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S5 S7 have S8: "(\<cn>B) = (\<cn>A) ⟷ B = A" by (rule MMI_neg11)
   have S9: "B = A ⟷ A = B" by (rule MMI_eqcom)
   from S8 S9 have S10: "A = B ⟷ (\<cn>B) = (\<cn>A)" by (rule MMI_bitr2)
   from S3 S10 have S11: "A\<ls>B ∨ A = B ⟷ 
   (\<cn>B)\<ls>(\<cn>A) ∨ (\<cn>B) = (\<cn>A)" by (rule MMI_orbi12i_orig)
   from A1 have S12: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S13: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S12 S13 have S14: "A\<lsq>B ⟷ A\<ls>B ∨ A = B" by (rule MMI_leloe)
   from A2 have S15: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S15 have S16: "(\<cn>B) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegcl)
   from A1 have S17: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S17 have S18: "(\<cn>A) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegcl)
   from S16 S18 have S19: "(\<cn>B)\<lsq>(\<cn>A) ⟷ 
   (\<cn>B)\<ls>(\<cn>A) ∨ (\<cn>B) = (\<cn>A)" by (rule MMI_leloe)
   from S11 S14 S19 show "A\<lsq>B ⟷ (\<cn>B)\<lsq>(\<cn>A)" by (rule MMI_3bitr4)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_ltnegcon2: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A\<ls>(\<cn>B) ⟷ B\<ls>(\<cn>A)"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S2 have S3: "(\<cn>B) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegcl)
   from S1 S3 have S4: "A\<ls>(\<cn>B) ⟷ (\<cn>(\<cn>B))\<ls>(\<cn>A)" by (rule MMI_ltneg)
   from A2 have S5: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S5 have S6: "B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S6 have S7: "(\<cn>(\<cn>B)) = B" by (rule MMI_negneg)
   from S7 have S8: "(\<cn>(\<cn>B))\<ls>(\<cn>A) ⟷ B\<ls>(\<cn>A)" by (rule MMI_breq1i)
   from S4 S8 show "A\<ls>(\<cn>B) ⟷ B\<ls>(\<cn>A)" by (rule MMI_bitr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mulgt0: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "𝟬\<ls>A ∧ 𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A⋅B"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   have S3: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬\<ls>A ∧ 𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A⋅B" by (rule MMI_axmulgt0)
   from S1 S2 S3 show "𝟬\<ls>A ∧ 𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A⋅B" by (rule MMI_mp2an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mulge0: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "𝟬\<lsq>A ∧ 𝟬\<lsq>B ⟶ 𝟬\<lsq>A⋅B"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "𝟬\<ls>A ∧ 𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A⋅B" by (rule MMI_mulgt0)
   have S4: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from A1 have S5: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S6: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S5 S6 have S7: "A⋅B ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_remulcl)
   from S4 S7 have S8: "𝟬\<ls>A⋅B ⟶ 𝟬\<lsq>A⋅B" by (rule MMI_ltle)
   from S3 S8 have S9: "𝟬\<ls>A ∧ 𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ 𝟬\<lsq>A⋅B" by (rule MMI_syl)
   have S10: "𝟬 = A ⟶ 𝟬⋅B = A⋅B" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   from A2 have S11: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S11 have S12: "B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S12 have S13: "𝟬⋅B = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_mul02)
   from S10 S13 have S14: "𝟬 = A ⟶ 𝟬 = A⋅B" by (rule MMI_syl5eqr)
   have S15: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from S7 have S16: "A⋅B ∈ ℝ" .
   from S15 S16 have S17: "𝟬 = A⋅B ⟶ 𝟬\<lsq>A⋅B" by (rule MMI_eqle)
   from S14 S17 have S18: "𝟬 = A ⟶ 𝟬\<lsq>A⋅B" by (rule MMI_syl)
   have S19: "𝟬 = B ⟶ A⋅𝟬 = A⋅B" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   from A1 have S20: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S20 have S21: "A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S21 have S22: "A⋅𝟬 = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_mul01)
   from S19 S22 have S23: "𝟬 = B ⟶ 𝟬 = A⋅B" by (rule MMI_syl5eqr)
   from S17 have S24: "𝟬 = A⋅B ⟶ 𝟬\<lsq>A⋅B" .
   from S23 S24 have S25: "𝟬 = B ⟶ 𝟬\<lsq>A⋅B" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S9 S18 S25 have S26: "(𝟬\<ls>A ∨ 𝟬 = A) ∧ (𝟬\<ls>B ∨ 𝟬 = B) ⟶ 𝟬\<lsq>A⋅B" by (rule MMI_ccase2)
   have S27: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from A1 have S28: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S27 S28 have S29: "𝟬\<lsq>A ⟷ 
   𝟬\<ls>A ∨ 𝟬 = A" by (rule MMI_leloe)
   have S30: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from A2 have S31: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S30 S31 have S32: "𝟬\<lsq>B ⟷ 
   𝟬\<ls>B ∨ 𝟬 = B" by (rule MMI_leloe)
   from S26 S29 S32 show "𝟬\<lsq>A ∧ 𝟬\<lsq>B ⟶ 𝟬\<lsq>A⋅B" by (rule MMI_syl2anb)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_mulgt0i: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ" and
    A3: "𝟬\<ls>A" and
    A4: "𝟬\<ls>B"   
   shows "𝟬\<ls>A⋅B"
proof -
   from A3 have S1: "𝟬\<ls>A".
   from A4 have S2: "𝟬\<ls>B".
   from A1 have S3: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S4: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S3 S4 have S5: "𝟬\<ls>A ∧ 𝟬\<ls>B ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A⋅B" by (rule MMI_mulgt0)
   from S1 S2 S5 show "𝟬\<ls>A⋅B" by (rule MMI_mp2an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_ltnr: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "¬(A\<ls>A)"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   have S2: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ ¬(A\<ls>A)" by (rule MMI_ltnrt)
   from S1 S2 show "¬(A\<ls>A)" by (rule MMI_ax_mp)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_leid: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "A\<lsq>A"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   have S2: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ A\<lsq>A" by (rule MMI_leidt)
   from S1 S2 show "A\<lsq>A" by (rule MMI_ax_mp)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_gt0ne0: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "𝟬\<ls>A ⟶ A ≠ 𝟬"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from A1 have S2: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "𝟬\<ls>A ⟶ ¬(𝟬 = A)" by (rule MMI_ltne)
   have S4: "𝟬 ≠ A ⟷ ¬(𝟬 = A)" by (rule MMI_df_ne)
   from S3 S4 have S5: "𝟬\<ls>A ⟶ 𝟬 ≠ A" by (rule MMI_sylibr)
   have S6: "A ≠ 𝟬 ⟷ 𝟬 ≠ A" by (rule MMI_necom)
   from S5 S6 show "𝟬\<ls>A ⟶ A ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_sylibr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_lesub0: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "𝟬\<lsq>A ∧ B\<lsq>B \<cs> A ⟷ A = 𝟬"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from A1 have S2: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S2 have S3: "(\<cn>A) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegcl)
   from A2 have S4: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S1 S3 S4 have S5: "𝟬\<lsq>(\<cn>A) ⟷ 
   B \<ca> 𝟬\<lsq>B \<ca> (\<cn>A)" by (rule MMI_leadd2)
   from A1 have S6: "A ∈ ℝ".
   have S7: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from S6 S7 have S8: "A\<lsq>𝟬 ⟷ (\<cn>𝟬)\<lsq>(\<cn>A)" by (rule MMI_leneg)
   have S9: "(\<cn>𝟬) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_neg0)
   from S9 have S10: "(\<cn>𝟬)\<lsq>(\<cn>A) ⟷ 𝟬\<lsq>(\<cn>A)" by (rule MMI_breq1i)
   from S8 S10 have S11: "𝟬\<lsq>(\<cn>A) ⟷ A\<lsq>𝟬" by (rule MMI_bitr2)
   from A2 have S12: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S12 have S13: "B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S13 have S14: "B \<ca> 𝟬 = B" by (rule MMI_addid1)
   from S13 have S15: "B ∈ ℂ" .
   from A1 have S16: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S16 have S17: "A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S15 S17 have S18: "B \<ca> (\<cn>A) = B \<cs> A" by (rule MMI_negsub)
   from S14 S18 have S19: "B \<ca> 𝟬\<lsq>B \<ca> (\<cn>A) ⟷ B\<lsq>B \<cs> A" by (rule MMI_breq12i)
   from S5 S11 S19 have S20: "B\<lsq>B \<cs> A ⟷ A\<lsq>𝟬" by (rule MMI_3bitr3r)
   from S20 have S21: "B\<lsq>B \<cs> A ∧ 𝟬\<lsq>A ⟷ 
   A\<lsq>𝟬 ∧ 𝟬\<lsq>A" by (rule MMI_anbi1i)
   have S22: "𝟬\<lsq>A ∧ B\<lsq>B \<cs> A ⟷ 
   B\<lsq>B \<cs> A ∧ 𝟬\<lsq>A" by (rule MMI_ancom)
   from A1 have S23: "A ∈ ℝ".
   have S24: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from S23 S24 have S25: "A = 𝟬 ⟷ 
   A\<lsq>𝟬 ∧ 𝟬\<lsq>A" by (rule MMI_letri3)
   from S21 S22 S25 show "𝟬\<lsq>A ∧ B\<lsq>B \<cs> A ⟷ A = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_3bitr4)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_msqgt0: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "¬(A = 𝟬) ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A⋅A"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   have S2: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "¬(A = 𝟬) ⟷ 
   A\<ls>𝟬 ∨ 𝟬\<ls>A" by (rule MMI_lttri2)
   from A1 have S4: "A ∈ ℝ".
   have S5: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from S4 S5 have S6: "A\<ls>𝟬 ⟷ (\<cn>𝟬)\<ls>(\<cn>A)" by (rule MMI_ltneg)
   have S7: "(\<cn>𝟬) = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_neg0)
   from S7 have S8: "(\<cn>𝟬)\<ls>(\<cn>A) ⟷ 𝟬\<ls>(\<cn>A)" by (rule MMI_breq1i)
   from S6 S8 have S9: "A\<ls>𝟬 ⟷ 𝟬\<ls>(\<cn>A)" by (rule MMI_bitr)
   from A1 have S10: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S10 have S11: "(\<cn>A) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegcl)
   from S11 have S12: "(\<cn>A) ∈ ℝ" .
   from S11 S12 have S13: "𝟬\<ls>(\<cn>A) ∧ 𝟬\<ls>(\<cn>A) ⟶ 
   𝟬\<ls>(\<cn>A)⋅(\<cn>A)" by (rule MMI_mulgt0)
   from S13 have S14: "𝟬\<ls>(\<cn>A) ⟶ 
   𝟬\<ls>(\<cn>A)⋅(\<cn>A)" by (rule MMI_anidms)
   from A1 have S15: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S15 have S16: "A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S16 have S17: "A ∈ ℂ" .
   from S16 S17 have S18: "(\<cn>A)⋅(\<cn>A) = A⋅A" by (rule MMI_mul2neg)
   from S14 S18 have S19: "𝟬\<ls>(\<cn>A) ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A⋅A" by (rule MMI_syl6breq)
   from S9 S19 have S20: "A\<ls>𝟬 ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A⋅A" by (rule MMI_sylbi)
   from A1 have S21: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A1 have S22: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S21 S22 have S23: "𝟬\<ls>A ∧ 𝟬\<ls>A ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A⋅A" by (rule MMI_mulgt0)
   from S23 have S24: "𝟬\<ls>A ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A⋅A" by (rule MMI_anidms)
   from S20 S24 have S25: "A\<ls>𝟬 ∨ 𝟬\<ls>A ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A⋅A" by (rule MMI_jaoi)
   from S3 S25 show "¬(A = 𝟬) ⟶ 𝟬\<ls>A⋅A" by (rule MMI_sylbi)
qed
