lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_lediv12it: 
   shows "((A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ A \<lsq> B) ∧ (C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ A\<cdiv>D \<lsq> B\<cdiv>C"
proof -
   have S1: "((A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ A \<lsq> B) ∧ (𝟭\<cdiv>D ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭\<cdiv>C ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> 𝟭\<cdiv>D ∧ 𝟭\<cdiv>D \<lsq> 𝟭\<cdiv>C ⟶ 
   A⋅(𝟭\<cdiv>D) \<lsq> B⋅(𝟭\<cdiv>C)" by (rule MMI_lemul12it)
   have S2: "D ∈ ℝ ∧ D ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 𝟭\<cdiv>D ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_rerecclt)
   have S3: "C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ ⟶ D ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_pm3_27)
   from S3 have S4: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ D ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   have S5: "D ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> D ⟶ D ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_gt0ne0t)
   from S4 have S6: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ D ∈ ℝ" .
   have S7: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   have S8: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> D" by (rule MMI_ltletrt)
   from S7 S8 have S9: "C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> D" by (rule MMI_mp3an1)
   from S9 have S10: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> D" by (rule MMI_imp)
   from S5 S6 S10 have S11: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ D ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   from S2 S4 S11 have S12: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 𝟭\<cdiv>D ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   have S13: "C ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ⟶ C ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_gt0ne0t)
   have S14: "C ∈ ℝ ∧ C ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 𝟭\<cdiv>C ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_rerecclt)
   from S13 S14 have S15: "C ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ⟶ 𝟭\<cdiv>C ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_syldan)
   from S15 have S16: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 𝟭\<cdiv>C ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ad2ant2r)
   from S12 S16 have S17: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>D ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭\<cdiv>C ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_jca)
   have S18: "D ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> D ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>D" by (rule MMI_recgt0t)
   from S4 have S19: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ D ∈ ℝ" .
   from S10 have S20: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> D" .
   from S18 S19 S20 have S21: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>D" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   have S22: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭\<cdiv>D ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>D ⟶ 𝟬 \<lsq> 𝟭\<cdiv>D" by (rule MMI_ltlet)
   have S23: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from S23 have S24: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_a1i)
   from S12 have S25: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 𝟭\<cdiv>D ∈ ℝ" .
   from S22 S24 S25 have S26: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>D ⟶ 𝟬 \<lsq> 𝟭\<cdiv>D" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   from S21 S26 have S27: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 𝟬 \<lsq> 𝟭\<cdiv>D" by (rule MMI_mpd)
   have S28: "𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ C \<lsq> D" by (rule MMI_pm3_27)
   from S28 have S29: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ C \<lsq> D" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   have S30: "𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> C" by (rule MMI_pm3_26)
   from S30 have S31: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> C" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S10 have S32: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> D" .
   from S31 S32 have S33: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> D" by (rule MMI_jca)
   have S34: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> D ⟶ 
   C \<lsq> D ⟷ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>D \<lsq> 𝟭\<cdiv>C" by (rule MMI_lerectOLD)
   from S33 S34 have S35: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 
   C \<lsq> D ⟷ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>D \<lsq> 𝟭\<cdiv>C" by (rule MMI_syldan)
   from S29 S35 have S36: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>D \<lsq> 𝟭\<cdiv>C" by (rule MMI_mpbid)
   from S27 S36 have S37: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> 𝟭\<cdiv>D ∧ 𝟭\<cdiv>D \<lsq> 𝟭\<cdiv>C" by (rule MMI_jca)
   from S17 S37 have S38: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 
   (𝟭\<cdiv>D ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭\<cdiv>C ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> 𝟭\<cdiv>D ∧ 𝟭\<cdiv>D \<lsq> 𝟭\<cdiv>C" by (rule MMI_jca)
   from S1 S38 have S39: "((A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ A \<lsq> B) ∧ (C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 
   A⋅(𝟭\<cdiv>D) \<lsq> B⋅(𝟭\<cdiv>C)" by (rule MMI_sylan2)
   have S40: "A ∈ ℂ ∧ D ∈ ℂ ∧ D ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>D = A⋅(𝟭\<cdiv>D)" by (rule MMI_divrect)
   have S41: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recnt)
   from S41 have S42: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ (C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   have S43: "D ∈ ℝ ⟶ D ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recnt)
   from S43 have S44: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ D ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_ad2antlr)
   from S44 have S45: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ (C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ D ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S11 have S46: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ D ≠ 𝟬" .
   from S46 have S47: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ (C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ D ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S40 S42 S45 S47 have S48: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ (C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>D = A⋅(𝟭\<cdiv>D)" by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   from S48 have S49: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ) ∧ (C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>D = A⋅(𝟭\<cdiv>D)" by (rule MMI_adantlr)
   from S49 have S50: "((A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ A \<lsq> B) ∧ (C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>D = A⋅(𝟭\<cdiv>D)" by (rule MMI_adantlr)
   have S51: "B ∈ ℂ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ∧ C ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
   B\<cdiv>C = B⋅(𝟭\<cdiv>C)" by (rule MMI_divrect)
   have S52: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recnt)
   from S52 have S53: "B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ⟶ B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   have S54: "C ∈ ℝ ⟶ C ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recnt)
   from S54 have S55: "B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ⟶ C ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_ad2antrl)
   from S13 have S56: "C ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ⟶ C ≠ 𝟬" .
   from S56 have S57: "B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ⟶ C ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S51 S53 S55 S57 have S58: "B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ⟶ 
   B\<cdiv>C = B⋅(𝟭\<cdiv>C)" by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   from S58 have S59: "B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 
   B\<cdiv>C = B⋅(𝟭\<cdiv>C)" by (rule MMI_adantrrr)
   from S59 have S60: "B ∈ ℝ ∧ (C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 
   B\<cdiv>C = B⋅(𝟭\<cdiv>C)" by (rule MMI_adantrlr)
   from S60 have S61: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ) ∧ (C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 
   B\<cdiv>C = B⋅(𝟭\<cdiv>C)" by (rule MMI_adantll)
   from S61 have S62: "((A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ A \<lsq> B) ∧ (C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ 
   B\<cdiv>C = B⋅(𝟭\<cdiv>C)" by (rule MMI_adantlr)
   from S39 S50 S62 show "((A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ A \<lsq> B) ∧ (C ∈ ℝ ∧ D ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ∧ C \<lsq> D ⟶ A\<cdiv>D \<lsq> B\<cdiv>C" by auto (*(rule MMI_3brtr4d)*)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_reclt1t: 
   shows "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   A \<ls> 𝟭 ⟷ 𝟭 \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>A"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   have S2: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_lt01)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_pm3_2i)
   have S4: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A) ∧ 𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   A \<ls> 𝟭 ⟷ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>𝟭 \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_ltrect)
   from S3 S4 have S5: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   A \<ls> 𝟭 ⟷ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>𝟭 \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_mpan2)
   have S6: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from S6 have S7: "𝟭\<cdiv>𝟭 = 𝟭" by (rule MMI_div1)
   from S7 have S8: "𝟭\<cdiv>𝟭 \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ⟷ 𝟭 \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_breq1i)
   from S5 S8 show "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   A \<ls> 𝟭 ⟷ 𝟭 \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_syl6bb)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_recgt1t: 
   shows "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ls> A ⟷ 𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ls> 𝟭"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   have S2: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_lt01)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_pm3_2i)
   have S4: "(𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭) ∧ A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ls> A ⟷ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>𝟭" by (rule MMI_ltrect)
   from S3 S4 have S5: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ls> A ⟷ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>𝟭" by (rule MMI_mpan)
   have S6: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from S6 have S7: "𝟭\<cdiv>𝟭 = 𝟭" by (rule MMI_div1)
   from S7 have S8: "𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>𝟭 ⟷ 𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_breq2i)
   from S5 S8 show "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ls> A ⟷ 𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_syl6bb)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_recgt1it: 
   shows "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ∧ 𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ls> 𝟭"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_lt01)
   have S2: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   have S3: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   have S4: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 ∧ 𝟭 \<ls> A ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_axlttrn)
   from S2 S3 S4 have S5: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 ∧ 𝟭 \<ls> A ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_mp3an12)
   from S1 S5 have S6: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ls> A ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_mpani)
   from S6 have S7: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_imdistani)
   have S8: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_recgt0t)
   from S7 S8 have S9: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭 \<ls> A ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_syl)
   have S10: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ls> A ⟷ 𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_recgt1t)
   from S10 have S11: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A) ∧ 𝟭 \<ls> A ⟶ 𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_biimpa)
   from S7 have S12: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A" .
   from S11 S12 have S13: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭 \<ls> A) ∧ 𝟭 \<ls> A ⟶ 𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_sylan)
   from S13 have S14: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭 \<ls> A ⟶ 𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_anabss3)
   from S9 S14 show "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ∧ 𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_jca)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_recp1lt1: 
   shows "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> A) \<ls> 𝟭"
proof -
   have S1: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ A \<ls> A \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_ltp1t)
   have S2: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recnt)
   have S3: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   have S4: "A ∈ ℂ ∧ 𝟭 ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   A \<ca> 𝟭 = 𝟭 \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_axaddcom)
   from S3 S4 have S5: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   A \<ca> 𝟭 = 𝟭 \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_mpan2)
   from S2 S5 have S6: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<ca> 𝟭 = 𝟭 \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S1 S6 have S7: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ A \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_breqtrd)
   from S7 have S8: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ A \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   have S9: "𝟭 \<ca> A ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ∧ 𝟭 \<ca> A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
   (A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> A))⋅(𝟭 \<ca> A) = A" by (rule MMI_divcan1t)
   have S10: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   have S11: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 𝟭 \<ca> A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_axaddrcl)
   from S10 S11 have S12: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 𝟭 \<ca> A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_mpan)
   from S12 have S13: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 𝟭 \<ca> A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   from S13 have S14: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ca> A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recnd)
   from S2 have S15: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ A ∈ ℂ" .
   from S15 have S16: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   have S17: "𝟭 \<ca> A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> A ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ca> A ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_gt0ne0t)
   from S13 have S18: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 𝟭 \<ca> A ∈ ℝ" .
   have S19: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   have S20: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_lt01)
   have S21: "(𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ A ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_addgtge0t)
   from S20 S21 have S22: "(𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ A ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_mpanr1)
   from S19 S22 have S23: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_mpanl1)
   from S17 S18 S23 have S24: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ca> A ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   from S9 S14 S16 S24 have S25: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 
   (A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> A))⋅(𝟭 \<ca> A) = A" by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   from S12 have S26: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 𝟭 \<ca> A ∈ ℝ" .
   from S26 have S27: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ca> A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recnd)
   have S28: "𝟭 \<ca> A ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   𝟭⋅(𝟭 \<ca> A) = 𝟭 \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_mulid2t)
   from S27 S28 have S29: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟭⋅(𝟭 \<ca> A) = 𝟭 \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S29 have S30: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 
   𝟭⋅(𝟭 \<ca> A) = 𝟭 \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   from S8 S25 S30 have S31: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 
   (A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> A))⋅(𝟭 \<ca> A) \<ls> 𝟭⋅(𝟭 \<ca> A)" by (rule MMI_3brtr4d)
   have S32: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   have S33: "(A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> A) ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭 \<ca> A ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> A ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> A) \<ls> 𝟭 ⟷ 
   (A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> A))⋅(𝟭 \<ca> A) \<ls> 𝟭⋅(𝟭 \<ca> A)" by (rule MMI_ltmul1t)
   from S32 S33 have S34: "(A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> A) ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭 \<ca> A ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> A ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> A) \<ls> 𝟭 ⟷ 
   (A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> A))⋅(𝟭 \<ca> A) \<ls> 𝟭⋅(𝟭 \<ca> A)" by (rule MMI_mp3anl2)
   have S35: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭 \<ca> A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭 \<ca> A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> A) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_redivclt)
   have S36: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_pm3_26)
   from S13 have S37: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 𝟭 \<ca> A ∈ ℝ" .
   from S24 have S38: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ca> A ≠ 𝟬" .
   from S35 S36 S37 S38 have S39: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> A) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   from S13 have S40: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 𝟭 \<ca> A ∈ ℝ" .
   from S39 S40 have S41: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> A) ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭 \<ca> A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_jca)
   from S23 have S42: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> A" .
   from S34 S41 S42 have S43: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> A) \<ls> 𝟭 ⟷ 
   (A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> A))⋅(𝟭 \<ca> A) \<ls> 𝟭⋅(𝟭 \<ca> A)" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   from S31 S43 show "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> A) \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_mpbird)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_recrecltt: 
   shows "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A) \<ls> 𝟭 ∧ 𝟭\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A) \<ls> A"
proof -
   have S1: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_recgt0t)
   have S2: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ A ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_gt0ne0t)
   have S3: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_rerecclt)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_syldan)
   have S5: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   have S6: "𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭 ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ⟷ 
   𝟭 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_ltaddpost)
   from S5 S6 have S7: "𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ⟷ 
   𝟭 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_mpan2)
   from S4 S7 have S8: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ⟷ 
   𝟭 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S1 S8 have S9: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_mpbid)
   have S10: "𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ⟷ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A) \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_recgt1t)
   from S4 have S11: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℝ" .
   have S12: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   have S13: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_axaddrcl)
   from S12 S13 have S14: "𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_mpan)
   from S11 S14 have S15: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S9 have S16: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" .
   have S17: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_lt01)
   from S15 have S18: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℝ" .
   have S19: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   have S20: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   have S21: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 ∧ 𝟭 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_axlttrn)
   from S19 S20 S21 have S22: "𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 ∧ 𝟭 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_mp3an12)
   from S18 S22 have S23: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 ∧ 𝟭 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S17 S23 have S24: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_mpani)
   from S16 S24 have S25: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_mpd)
   from S10 S15 S25 have S26: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ⟷ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A) \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   from S9 S26 have S27: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A) \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_mpbid)
   have S28: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_lt01)
   from S4 have S29: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℝ" .
   have S30: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   have S31: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 ⟷ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_ltaddpost)
   from S30 S31 have S32: "𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 ⟷ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_mpan)
   from S29 S32 have S33: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 ⟷ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S28 S33 have S34: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_mpbii)
   from S4 have S35: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℝ" .
   from S35 have S36: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recnd)
   have S37: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   have S38: "𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℂ ∧ 𝟭 ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ca> 𝟭 = 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_axaddcom)
   from S37 S38 have S39: "𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ca> 𝟭 = 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_mpan2)
   from S36 S39 have S40: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ca> 𝟭 = 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S34 S40 have S41: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_breqtrd)
   have S42: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ⟶ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ⟷ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A) \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_ltrec1t)
   have S43: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_pm3_26)
   from S15 have S44: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℝ" .
   from S43 S44 have S45: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_jca)
   have S46: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_pm3_27)
   from S25 have S47: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" .
   from S46 S47 have S48: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> A ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_jca)
   from S42 S45 S48 have S49: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>A \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A ⟷ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A) \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   from S41 S49 have S50: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A) \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_mpbid)
   from S27 S50 show "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A) \<ls> 𝟭 ∧ 𝟭\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭\<cdiv>A) \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_jca)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_le2msqt: 
   shows "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> B ⟷ A⋅A \<lsq> B⋅B"
proof -
   have S1: "A =  if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟷ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))" by (rule MMI_breq2)
   from S1 have S2: "A =  if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟷ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B" by (rule MMI_anbi1d)
   have S3: "A =  if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> B ⟷ 
   ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) \<lsq> B" by (rule MMI_breq1)
   have S4: "A =  if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬) ∧ A =  if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   A⋅A = ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))⋅( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))" by (rule MMI_opreq12)
   from S4 have S5: "A =  if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   A⋅A = ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))⋅( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))" by (rule MMI_anidms)
   from S5 have S6: "A =  if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   A⋅A \<lsq> B⋅B ⟷ 
   ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))⋅( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) \<lsq> B⋅B" by (rule MMI_breq1d)
   from S3 S6 have S7: "A =  if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   (A \<lsq> B ⟷ A⋅A \<lsq> B⋅B) ⟷ 
   ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) \<lsq> B ⟷ 
   ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))⋅( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) \<lsq> B⋅B" by (rule MMI_bibi12d)
   from S2 S7 have S8: "A =  if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   (𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> B ⟷ A⋅A \<lsq> B⋅B) ⟷ 
   (𝟬 \<lsq> ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) \<lsq> B ⟷ 
   ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))⋅( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) \<lsq> B⋅B)" by (rule MMI_imbi12d)
   have S9: "B =  if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟷ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> ( if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬))" by (rule MMI_breq2)
   from S9 have S10: "B =  if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟷ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> ( if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬))" by (rule MMI_anbi2d)
   have S11: "B =  if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) \<lsq> B ⟷ 
   ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) \<lsq> ( if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬))" by (rule MMI_breq2)
   have S12: "B =  if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬) ∧ B =  if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   B⋅B = ( if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬))⋅( if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬))" by (rule MMI_opreq12)
   from S12 have S13: "B =  if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   B⋅B = ( if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬))⋅( if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬))" by (rule MMI_anidms)
   from S13 have S14: "B =  if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))⋅( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) \<lsq> B⋅B ⟷ 
   ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))⋅( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) \<lsq> ( if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬))⋅( if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬))" by (rule MMI_breq2d)
   from S11 S14 have S15: "B =  if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   (( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) \<lsq> B ⟷ 
   ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))⋅( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) \<lsq> B⋅B) ⟷ 
   ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) \<lsq> ( if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬)) ⟷ 
   ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))⋅( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) \<lsq> ( if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬))⋅( if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬))" by (rule MMI_bibi12d)
   from S10 S15 have S16: "B =  if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   (𝟬 \<lsq> ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) \<lsq> B ⟷ 
   ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))⋅( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) \<lsq> B⋅B) ⟷ 
   (𝟬 \<lsq> ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> ( if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬)) ⟶ 
   ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) \<lsq> ( if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬)) ⟷ 
   ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))⋅( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) \<lsq> ( if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬))⋅( if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬)))" by (rule MMI_imbi12d)
   have S17: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from S17 have S18: " if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   have S19: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from S19 have S20: " if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   from S18 S20 have S21: "𝟬 \<lsq> ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> ( if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬)) ⟶ 
   ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) \<lsq> ( if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬)) ⟷ 
   ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))⋅( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) \<lsq> ( if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬))⋅( if(B ∈ ℝ, B, 𝟬))" by (rule MMI_le2msq)
   from S8 S16 S21 have S22: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> B ⟷ A⋅A \<lsq> B⋅B" by (rule MMI_dedth2h)
   from S22 have S23: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> B ⟷ A⋅A \<lsq> B⋅B" by (rule MMI_imp)
   from S23 show "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> B ⟷ A⋅A \<lsq> B⋅B" by (rule MMI_an4s)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_halfpos: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "𝟬 \<ls> A ⟷ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from A1 have S2: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A1 have S3: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S1 S2 S3 have S4: "𝟬 \<ls> A ⟷ 
   𝟬 \<ca> A \<ls> A \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_ltadd1)
   from A1 have S5: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S5 have S6: "A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S6 have S7: "𝟬 \<ca> A = A" by (rule MMI_addid2)
   from S6 have S8: "A ∈ ℂ" .
   from S8 have S9: "(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)⋅A = A \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_1p1times)
   from S9 have S10: "A \<ca> A = (𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)⋅A" by (rule MMI_eqcomi)
   from S7 S10 have S11: "𝟬 \<ca> A \<ls> A \<ca> A ⟷ 
   A \<ls> (𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)⋅A" by (rule MMI_breq12i)
   from A1 have S12: "A ∈ ℝ".
   have S13: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   have S14: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   from S13 S14 have S15: "𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_readdcl)
   from A1 have S16: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S15 S16 have S17: "(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)⋅A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_remulcl)
   from S15 have S18: "𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   have S19: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   have S20: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   have S21: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_lt01)
   have S22: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_lt01)
   from S19 S20 S21 S22 have S23: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_addgt0i)
   from S12 S17 S18 S23 have S24: "A \<ls> (𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)⋅A ⟷ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> (𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)⋅A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_ltdiv1i)
   from S11 S24 have S25: "𝟬 \<ca> A \<ls> A \<ca> A ⟷ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> (𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)⋅A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_bitr)
   have S26: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   have S27: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from S26 S27 have S28: "𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_addcl)
   from S6 have S29: "A ∈ ℂ" .
   from S15 have S30: "𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   from S23 have S31: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭" .
   from S30 S31 have S32: "𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭 ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_gt0ne0i)
   from S28 S29 S32 have S33: "(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)⋅A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) = A" by (rule MMI_divcan3)
   from S33 have S34: "A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> (𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)⋅A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ⟷ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_breq2i)
   from S4 S25 S34 show "𝟬 \<ls> A ⟷ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_3bitr)
qed

(********* 481-489*******************************)


lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_ledivp1t: 
   shows "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   (A\<cdiv>(B \<ca> 𝟭))⋅B \<lsq> A"
proof -
   have S1: "(B ∈ ℝ ∧ B \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ A\<cdiv>(B \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A\<cdiv>(B \<ca> 𝟭) ∧ B \<lsq> B \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   (A\<cdiv>(B \<ca> 𝟭))⋅B \<lsq> (A\<cdiv>(B \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(B \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_lemul2it)
   have S2: "B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ B ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_pm3_26)
   from S2 have S3: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ B ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   have S4: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ B \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_peano2re)
   from S4 have S5: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ B \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ad2antrl)
   have S6: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ B \<ca> 𝟭 ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>(B \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_redivclt)
   have S7: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_pm3_26)
   from S4 have S8: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ B \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   from S8 have S9: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ B \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ad2antrl)
   have S10: "B \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> B \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   B \<ca> 𝟭 ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_gt0ne0t)
   from S4 have S11: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ B \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   from S11 have S12: "B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ B \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   have S13: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ B \<ls> B \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_ltp1t)
   from S4 have S14: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ B \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   have S15: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   have S16: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ B \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> B ∧ B \<ls> B \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> B \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_lelttrt)
   from S15 S16 have S17: "B ∈ ℝ ∧ B \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> B ∧ B \<ls> B \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> B \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_mp3an1)
   from S14 S17 have S18: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> B ∧ B \<ls> B \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> B \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_mpdan)
   from S13 S18 have S19: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> B \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_mpan2d)
   from S19 have S20: "B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> B \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_imp)
   from S10 S12 S20 have S21: "B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   B \<ca> 𝟭 ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   from S21 have S22: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   B \<ca> 𝟭 ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S6 S7 S9 S22 have S23: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>(B \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   from S23 have S24: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>(B \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_adantlr)
   from S3 S5 S24 have S25: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   B ∈ ℝ ∧ B \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ A\<cdiv>(B \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_3jca)
   have S26: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ B \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> B \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> A\<cdiv>(B \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_divge0t)
   have S27: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_pm3_26)
   from S12 have S28: "B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ B \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   from S27 S28 have S29: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   A ∈ ℝ ∧ B \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_anim12i)
   have S30: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 𝟬 \<lsq> A" by (rule MMI_pm3_27)
   from S20 have S31: "B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> B \<ca> 𝟭" .
   from S30 S31 have S32: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> B \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_anim12i)
   from S26 S29 S32 have S33: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> A\<cdiv>(B \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   from S13 have S34: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ B \<ls> B \<ca> 𝟭" .
   from S34 have S35: "B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ B \<ls> B \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   from S4 have S36: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ B \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   have S37: "B ∈ ℝ ∧ B \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   B \<ls> B \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ B \<lsq> B \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_ltlet)
   from S36 S37 have S38: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   B \<ls> B \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ B \<lsq> B \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_mpdan)
   from S38 have S39: "B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   B \<ls> B \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ B \<lsq> B \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   from S35 S39 have S40: "B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ B \<lsq> B \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_mpd)
   from S40 have S41: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ B \<lsq> B \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S33 S41 have S42: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> A\<cdiv>(B \<ca> 𝟭) ∧ B \<lsq> B \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_jca)
   from S1 S25 S42 have S43: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   (A\<cdiv>(B \<ca> 𝟭))⋅B \<lsq> (A\<cdiv>(B \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(B \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   have S44: "B \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ∧ B \<ca> 𝟭 ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
   (A\<cdiv>(B \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(B \<ca> 𝟭) = A" by (rule MMI_divcan1t)
   from S4 have S45: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ B \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   from S45 have S46: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   B \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recnd)
   from S46 have S47: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   B \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_ad2antrl)
   have S48: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recnt)
   from S48 have S49: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_ad2antrr)
   from S21 have S50: "B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   B \<ca> 𝟭 ≠ 𝟬" .
   from S50 have S51: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   B \<ca> 𝟭 ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S44 S47 S49 S51 have S52: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   (A\<cdiv>(B \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(B \<ca> 𝟭) = A" by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   from S43 S52 show "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   (A\<cdiv>(B \<ca> 𝟭))⋅B \<lsq> A" by auto (*(rule MMI_breqtrd)*)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_ledivp1: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> C ∧ A \<lsq> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ A⋅C \<lsq> B"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S2: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "A⋅C ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_remulcl)
   from A1 have S4: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S5: "C ∈ ℝ".
   have S6: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   from S5 S6 have S7: "C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_readdcl)
   from S4 S7 have S8: "A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_remulcl)
   from A2 have S9: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S3 S8 S9 have S10: "A⋅C \<lsq> A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) ∧ A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) \<lsq> B ⟶ A⋅C \<lsq> B" by (rule MMI_letr)
   from A3 have S11: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S7 have S12: "C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   from A3 have S13: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S13 have S14: "C \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_ltp1)
   from S11 S12 S14 have S15: "C \<lsq> C \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_ltlei)
   from A3 have S16: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S7 have S17: "C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   from A1 have S18: "A ∈ ℝ".
   have S19: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ A ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ C \<lsq> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   A⋅C \<lsq> A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_lemul2it)
   from S19 have S20: "C ∈ ℝ ∧ C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ C \<lsq> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   A⋅C \<lsq> A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_ex)
   from S16 S17 S18 S20 have S21: "𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ C \<lsq> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   A⋅C \<lsq> A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_mp3an)
   from S15 S21 have S22: "𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 
   A⋅C \<lsq> A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_mpan2)
   from S22 have S23: "𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> C ∧ A \<lsq> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
   A⋅C \<lsq> A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_3ad2ant1)
   from S14 have S24: "C \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭" .
   have S25: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from A3 have S26: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S7 have S27: "C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   from S25 S26 S27 have S28: "𝟬 \<lsq> C ∧ C \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_lelttr)
   from S24 S28 have S29: "𝟬 \<lsq> C ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_mpan2)
   from S7 have S30: "C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   from S30 have S31: "𝟬 \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   C \<ca> 𝟭 ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_gt0ne0)
   from A2 have S32: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S7 have S33: "C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   from S32 S33 have S34: "C \<ca> 𝟭 ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
   B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_redivclz)
   from S31 S34 have S35: "𝟬 \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S7 have S36: "C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   from A1 have S37: "A ∈ ℝ".
   have S38: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ ∧ C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟷ 
   A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) \<lsq> (B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_lemul1t)
   from S37 S38 have S39: "(B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ ∧ C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟷ 
   A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) \<lsq> (B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_mp3anl1)
   from S36 S39 have S40: "B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟷ 
   A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) \<lsq> (B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_mpanl2)
   from S35 S40 have S41: "𝟬 \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟷ 
   A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) \<lsq> (B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_mpancom)
   from S41 have S42: "𝟬 \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
   A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) \<lsq> (B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_biimpd)
   from S29 S42 have S43: "𝟬 \<lsq> C ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
   A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) \<lsq> (B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S43 have S44: "𝟬 \<lsq> C ∧ A \<lsq> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
   A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) \<lsq> (B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_imp)
   from S29 have S45: "𝟬 \<lsq> C ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭" .
   from S31 have S46: "𝟬 \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   C \<ca> 𝟭 ≠ 𝟬" .
   from S7 have S47: "C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   from S47 have S48: "C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from A2 have S49: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S49 have S50: "B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S48 S50 have S51: "C \<ca> 𝟭 ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
   (B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) = B" by (rule MMI_divcan1z)
   from S45 S46 S51 have S52: "𝟬 \<lsq> C ⟶ 
   (B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) = B" by (rule MMI_3syl)
   from S52 have S53: "𝟬 \<lsq> C ∧ A \<lsq> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
   (B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) = B" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   from S44 S53 have S54: "𝟬 \<lsq> C ∧ A \<lsq> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
   A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) \<lsq> B" by auto (*(rule MMI_breqtrd)*)
   from S54 have S55: "𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> C ∧ A \<lsq> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
   A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) \<lsq> B" by (rule MMI_3adant1)
   from S10 S23 S55 show "𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> C ∧ A \<lsq> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ A⋅C \<lsq> B" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_ltdivp1: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℝ"   
   shows "𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> C ∧ A \<ls> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ A⋅C \<ls> B"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S2: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "A⋅C ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_remulcl)
   from A1 have S4: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S5: "C ∈ ℝ".
   have S6: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   from S5 S6 have S7: "C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_readdcl)
   from S4 S7 have S8: "A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_remulcl)
   from A2 have S9: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S3 S8 S9 have S10: "A⋅C \<lsq> A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) ∧ A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B ⟶ A⋅C \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_lelttr)
   from A3 have S11: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S7 have S12: "C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   from A3 have S13: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S13 have S14: "C \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_ltp1)
   from S11 S12 S14 have S15: "C \<lsq> C \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_ltlei)
   from A3 have S16: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S7 have S17: "C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   from A1 have S18: "A ∈ ℝ".
   have S19: "(C ∈ ℝ ∧ C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ A ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ C \<lsq> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   A⋅C \<lsq> A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_lemul2it)
   from S19 have S20: "C ∈ ℝ ∧ C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ C \<lsq> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   A⋅C \<lsq> A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_ex)
   from S16 S17 S18 S20 have S21: "𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ C \<lsq> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   A⋅C \<lsq> A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_mp3an)
   from S15 S21 have S22: "𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 
   A⋅C \<lsq> A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_mpan2)
   from S22 have S23: "𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> C ∧ A \<ls> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
   A⋅C \<lsq> A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_3ad2ant1)
   from S14 have S24: "C \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭" .
   have S25: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from A3 have S26: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S7 have S27: "C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   from S25 S26 S27 have S28: "𝟬 \<lsq> C ∧ C \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_lelttr)
   from S24 S28 have S29: "𝟬 \<lsq> C ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_mpan2)
   from S7 have S30: "C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   from S30 have S31: "𝟬 \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   C \<ca> 𝟭 ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_gt0ne0)
   from A2 have S32: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S7 have S33: "C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   from S32 S33 have S34: "C \<ca> 𝟭 ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
   B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_redivclz)
   from S31 S34 have S35: "𝟬 \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S7 have S36: "C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   from A1 have S37: "A ∈ ℝ".
   have S38: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ ∧ C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   A \<ls> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟷ 
   A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> (B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_ltmul1t)
   from S37 S38 have S39: "(B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ ∧ C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   A \<ls> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟷ 
   A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> (B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_mp3anl1)
   from S36 S39 have S40: "B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   A \<ls> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟷ 
   A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> (B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_mpanl2)
   from S35 S40 have S41: "𝟬 \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   A \<ls> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟷ 
   A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> (B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_mpancom)
   from S41 have S42: "𝟬 \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   A \<ls> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
   A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> (B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_biimpd)
   from S29 S42 have S43: "𝟬 \<lsq> C ⟶ 
   A \<ls> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
   A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> (B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S43 have S44: "𝟬 \<lsq> C ∧ A \<ls> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
   A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> (B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_imp)
   from S29 have S45: "𝟬 \<lsq> C ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭" .
   from S31 have S46: "𝟬 \<ls> C \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
   C \<ca> 𝟭 ≠ 𝟬" .
   from S7 have S47: "C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   from S47 have S48: "C \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from A2 have S49: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S49 have S50: "B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S48 S50 have S51: "C \<ca> 𝟭 ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
   (B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) = B" by (rule MMI_divcan1z)
   from S45 S46 S51 have S52: "𝟬 \<lsq> C ⟶ 
   (B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) = B" by (rule MMI_3syl)
   from S52 have S53: "𝟬 \<lsq> C ∧ A \<ls> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
   (B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭))⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) = B" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   from S44 S53 have S54: "𝟬 \<lsq> C ∧ A \<ls> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
   A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_breqtrd)
   from S54 have S55: "𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> C ∧ A \<ls> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
   A⋅(C \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_3adant1)
   from S10 S23 S55 show "𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> C ∧ A \<ls> B\<cdiv>(C \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ A⋅C \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_posex: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ" and
    A3: "𝟬 \<ls> A" and
    A4: "𝟬 \<ls> B"   
   shows " ∃x∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> x ∧ x \<ls> A ∧ x \<ls> B"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S2: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S1 S2 have S3: "¬(A = B) ⟷ A \<ls> B ∨ B \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_lttri2)
   from S3 have S4: "¬(A = B) ⟶ A \<ls> B ∨ B \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_biimp)
   from S4 have S5: "A = B ∨ A \<ls> B ∨ B \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_orri)
   have S6: "A = B ∨ A \<ls> B ∨ B \<ls> A ⟷ 
   A \<ls> B ∨ A = B ∨ B \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_or12)
   from S5 S6 have S7: "A \<ls> B ∨ A = B ∨ B \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_mpbi)
   from A3 have S8: "𝟬 \<ls> A".
   from A1 have S9: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S9 have S10: "𝟬 \<ls> A ⟷ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_halfpos)
   from S8 S10 have S11: "A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_mpbi)
   from A1 have S12: "A ∈ ℝ".
   have S13: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   have S14: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   from S13 S14 have S15: "𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_readdcl)
   from S15 have S16: "𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   have S17: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   have S18: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   have S19: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_lt01)
   have S20: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_lt01)
   from S17 S18 S19 S20 have S21: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_addgt0i)
   from S16 S21 have S22: "𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭 ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_gt0ne0i)
   from S12 S15 S22 have S23: "A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_redivcl)
   from A1 have S24: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S25: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S23 S24 S25 have S26: "A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A ∧ A \<ls> B ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_lttr)
   from S11 S26 have S27: "A \<ls> B ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_mpan)
   from S11 have S28: "A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A" .
   from S27 S28 have S29: "A \<ls> B ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A ∧ A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_jctil)
   from A1 have S30: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S15 have S31: "𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   from A3 have S32: "𝟬 \<ls> A".
   from S21 have S33: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭" .
   from S30 S31 S32 S33 have S34: "𝟬 \<ls> A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_divgt0i)
   from S29 S34 have S35: "A \<ls> B ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ∧ A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A ∧ A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_jctil)
   from S23 have S36: "A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ" .
   from S35 S36 have S37: "A \<ls> B ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ∧ A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A ∧ A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" 
     by (rule MMI_jctil)
   { fix x
     have S38: "x = A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
       𝟬 \<ls> x ⟷ 
       𝟬 \<ls> A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_breq2)
     have S39: "x = A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
       x \<ls> A ⟷ 
       A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_breq1)
     have S40: "x = A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
       x \<ls> B ⟷ 
       A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_breq1)
     from S39 S40 have S41: "x = A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
       x \<ls> A ∧ x \<ls> B ⟷ 
       A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A ∧ A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_anbi12d)
     from S38 S41 have  "x = A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
       𝟬 \<ls> x ∧ x \<ls> A ∧ x \<ls> B ⟷ 
       𝟬 \<ls> A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ∧ A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A ∧ A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_anbi12d)
   } then have S42: "∀x.  x = A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
       𝟬 \<ls> x ∧ x \<ls> A ∧ x \<ls> B ⟷ 
       𝟬 \<ls> A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ∧ A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A ∧ A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" by simp
   from S42 have S43: 
     "A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ∧ A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A ∧ A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B ⟶
     ( ∃x∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> x ∧ x \<ls> A ∧ x \<ls> B)" by (rule MMI_rcla4ev)
   from S37 S43 have S44: "A \<ls> B ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> x ∧ x \<ls> A ∧ x \<ls> B)" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from A4 have S45: "𝟬 \<ls> B".
   from A2 have S46: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S46 have S47: "𝟬 \<ls> B ⟷ 
   B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_halfpos)
   from S45 S47 have S48: "B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_mpbi)
   have S49: "A = B ⟶ 
   B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A ⟷ 
   B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_breq2)
   from S48 S49 have S50: "A = B ⟶ 
   B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_mpbiri)
   from S48 have S51: "B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" .
   from A2 have S52: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S15 have S53: "𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   from S22 have S54: "𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭 ≠ 𝟬" .
   from S52 S53 S54 have S55: "B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_redivcl)
   from A2 have S56: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from A1 have S57: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from S55 S56 S57 have S58: "B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B ∧ B \<ls> A ⟶ 
   B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_lttr)
   from S51 S58 have S59: "B \<ls> A ⟶ 
   B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_mpan)
   from S50 S59 have S60: "A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ⟶ 
   B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_jaoi)
   from S48 have S61: "B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" .
   from S60 S61 have S62: "A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ⟶ 
   B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A ∧ B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_jctir)
   from A2 have S63: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from S15 have S64: "𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
   from A4 have S65: "𝟬 \<ls> B".
   from S21 have S66: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭" .
   from S63 S64 S65 S66 have S67: "𝟬 \<ls> B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_divgt0i)
   from S62 S67 have S68: "A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ∧ B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A ∧ B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_jctil)
   from S55 have S69: "B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ" .
   from S68 S69 have S70: "A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ⟶ 
   B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ∧ B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A ∧ B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_jctil)
   { fix x
     have S71: "x = B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
       𝟬 \<ls> x ⟷ 
       𝟬 \<ls> B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_breq2)
     have S72: "x = B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
       x \<ls> A ⟷ 
       B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_breq1)
     have S73: "x = B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
       x \<ls> B ⟷ 
       B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_breq1)
     from S72 S73 have S74: "x = B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
       x \<ls> A ∧ x \<ls> B ⟷ 
       B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A ∧ B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_anbi12d)
     from S71 S74 have  "x = B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
       𝟬 \<ls> x ∧ x \<ls> A ∧ x \<ls> B ⟷ 
       𝟬 \<ls> B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ∧ B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A ∧ B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_anbi12d)
   } then have S75: "∀ x. x = B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
       𝟬 \<ls> x ∧ x \<ls> A ∧ x \<ls> B ⟷ 
       𝟬 \<ls> B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ∧ B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A ∧ B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B" by simp
     from S75 have S76: "B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) ∧ B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A ∧ B\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> B ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> x ∧ x \<ls> A ∧ x \<ls> B)" by (rule MMI_rcla4ev)
   from S70 S76 have S77: "A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> x ∧ x \<ls> A ∧ x \<ls> B)" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S44 S77 have S78: "A \<ls> B ∨ A = B ∨ B \<ls> A ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> x ∧ x \<ls> A ∧ x \<ls> B)" by (rule MMI_jaoi)
   from S7 S78 show " ∃x∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> x ∧ x \<ls> A ∧ x \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_ax_mp)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_max1: 
   shows "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A))"
proof -
   have S1: "¬(A \<lsq> B) ⟶  if(A \<lsq> B, B, A) = A" by (rule MMI_iffalse)
   from S1 have S2: "¬(A \<lsq> B) ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) ⟷ A \<lsq> A" by (rule MMI_breq2d)
   have S3: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ A \<lsq> A" by (rule MMI_leidt)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "¬(A \<lsq> B) ⟶ 
   A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A))" by (rule MMI_syl5bir)
   from S4 have S5: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   ¬(A \<lsq> B) ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A))" by (rule MMI_com12)
   have S6: "A \<lsq> B ⟶ A \<lsq> B" by (rule MMI_id)
   have S7: "A \<lsq> B ⟶  if(A \<lsq> B, B, A) = B" by (rule MMI_iftrue)
   from S6 S7 have S8: "A \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A))" by auto (*by (rule MMI_breqtrrd)*)
   from S5 S8 have S9: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A))" by (rule MMI_pm2_61d2)
   from S9 show "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A))" by (rule MMI_adantr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_max1ALT: 
   shows "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A))"
proof -
   have S1: "¬(A \<lsq> B) ⟶  if(A \<lsq> B, B, A) = A" by (rule MMI_iffalse)
   from S1 have S2: "¬(A \<lsq> B) ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) ⟷ A \<lsq> A" by (rule MMI_breq2d)
   have S3: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ A \<lsq> A" by (rule MMI_leidt)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "¬(A \<lsq> B) ⟶ 
   A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A))" by (rule MMI_syl5bir)
   from S4 have S5: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   ¬(A \<lsq> B) ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A))" by (rule MMI_com12)
   have S6: "A \<lsq> B ⟶ A \<lsq> B" by (rule MMI_id)
   have S7: "A \<lsq> B ⟶  if(A \<lsq> B, B, A) = B" by (rule MMI_iftrue)
   from S6 S7 have S8: "A \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A))" by simp (*by (rule MMI_breqtrrd)*)
   from S5 S8 show "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A))" by (rule MMI_pm2_61d2)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_max2: 
   shows "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   B \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A))"
proof -
   have S1: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ B \<lsq> B" by (rule MMI_leidt)
   from S1 have S2: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ) ∧ A \<lsq> B ⟶ B \<lsq> B" by (rule MMI_ad2antlr)
   have S3: "A \<lsq> B ⟶  if(A \<lsq> B, B, A) = B" by (rule MMI_iftrue)
   from S3 have S4: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ) ∧ A \<lsq> B ⟶  if(A \<lsq> B, B, A) = B" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S2 S4 have S5: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ) ∧ A \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   B \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A))" by simp(*by (rule MMI_breqtrrd)*)
   have S6: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ A \<lsq> B ∨ B \<lsq> A" by (rule MMI_letrit)
   from S6 have S7: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ) ∧ ¬(A \<lsq> B) ⟶ B \<lsq> A" by (rule MMI_orcanai)
   have S8: "¬(A \<lsq> B) ⟶  if(A \<lsq> B, B, A) = A" by (rule MMI_iffalse)
   from S8 have S9: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ) ∧ ¬(A \<lsq> B) ⟶  if(A \<lsq> B, B, A) = A" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S7 S9 have S10: "(A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ) ∧ ¬(A \<lsq> B) ⟶ 
   B \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A))" by simp (*by (rule MMI_breqtrrd)*)
   from S5 S10 show "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   B \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A))" by (rule MMI_pm2_61dan)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_maxlet: 
   shows "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) \<lsq> C ⟷ A \<lsq> C ∧ B \<lsq> C"
proof -
   have S1: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A))" by (rule MMI_max1)
   from S1 have S2: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A))" by (rule MMI_3adant3)
   have S3: "A ∈ ℝ ∧  if(A \<lsq> B, B, A) ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) ∧ ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) \<lsq> C ⟶ A \<lsq> C" by (rule MMI_letrt)
   have S4: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ⟶ A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_3simp1)
   have S5: "B ∈ ℝ ∧ A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
    if(A \<lsq> B, B, A) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ifcl)
   from S5 have S6: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
    if(A \<lsq> B, B, A) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ancoms)
   from S6 have S7: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
    if(A \<lsq> B, B, A) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_3adant3)
   have S8: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ⟶ C ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_3simp3)
   from S3 S4 S7 S8 have S9: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) ∧ ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) \<lsq> C ⟶ A \<lsq> C" by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   from S2 S9 have S10: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) \<lsq> C ⟶ A \<lsq> C" by (rule MMI_mpand)
   have S11: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   B \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A))" by (rule MMI_max2)
   from S11 have S12: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   B \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A))" by (rule MMI_3adant3)
   have S13: "B ∈ ℝ ∧  if(A \<lsq> B, B, A) ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   B \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) ∧ ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) \<lsq> C ⟶ B \<lsq> C" by (rule MMI_letrt)
   have S14: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ⟶ B ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_3simp2)
   from S7 have S15: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
    if(A \<lsq> B, B, A) ∈ ℝ" .
   from S8 have S16: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ⟶ C ∈ ℝ" .
   from S13 S14 S15 S16 have S17: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   B \<lsq> ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) ∧ ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) \<lsq> C ⟶ B \<lsq> C" by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   from S12 S17 have S18: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) \<lsq> C ⟶ B \<lsq> C" by (rule MMI_mpand)
   from S10 S18 have S19: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) \<lsq> C ⟶ A \<lsq> C ∧ B \<lsq> C" by (rule MMI_jcad)
   have S20: "A \<lsq> B ⟶  if(A \<lsq> B, B, A) = B" by (rule MMI_iftrue)
   from S20 have S21: "A \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) \<lsq> C ⟷ B \<lsq> C" by (rule MMI_breq1d)
   from S21 have S22: "A \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   B \<lsq> C ⟶ 
   ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) \<lsq> C" by (rule MMI_biimprd)
   from S22 have S23: "A \<lsq> B ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> C ∧ B \<lsq> C ⟶ 
   ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) \<lsq> C" by (rule MMI_adantld)
   have S24: "¬(A \<lsq> B) ⟶  if(A \<lsq> B, B, A) = A" by (rule MMI_iffalse)
   from S24 have S25: "¬(A \<lsq> B) ⟶ 
   ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) \<lsq> C ⟷ A \<lsq> C" by (rule MMI_breq1d)
   from S25 have S26: "¬(A \<lsq> B) ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> C ⟶ 
   ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) \<lsq> C" by (rule MMI_biimprd)
   from S26 have S27: "¬(A \<lsq> B) ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> C ∧ B \<lsq> C ⟶ 
   ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) \<lsq> C" by (rule MMI_adantrd)
   from S23 S27 have S28: "A \<lsq> C ∧ B \<lsq> C ⟶ 
   ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) \<lsq> C" by (rule MMI_pm2_61i)
   from S28 have S29: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<lsq> C ∧ B \<lsq> C ⟶ 
   ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) \<lsq> C" by (rule MMI_a1i)
   from S19 S29 show "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ C ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   ( if(A \<lsq> B, B, A)) \<lsq> C ⟷ A \<lsq> C ∧ B \<lsq> C" by (rule MMI_impbid)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_squeeze0: 
   shows "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ (∀x∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> x ⟶ A \<ls> x) ⟶ A = 𝟬"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   have S2: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ ∧ A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟷ 
   𝟬 \<ls> A ∨ 𝟬 = A" by (rule MMI_leloet)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟷ 
   𝟬 \<ls> A ∨ 𝟬 = A" by (rule MMI_mpan)
   have S4: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ ¬(A \<ls> A)" by (rule MMI_ltnrt)
   from S4 have S5: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<ls> A ⟶ A = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_pm2_21d)
   from S5 have S6: "A \<ls> A ⟶ 
   A ∈ ℝ ⟶ A = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_com12)
   from S6 have S7: "(𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ A \<ls> A) ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   A ∈ ℝ ⟶ A = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_imim2i)
   from S7 have S8: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   (𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ A \<ls> A) ⟶ A = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_com13)
   { fix x
     have S9: "x = A ⟶ 
       𝟬 \<ls> x ⟷ 𝟬 \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_breq2)
     have S10: "x = A ⟶ 
       A \<ls> x ⟷ A \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_breq2)
     from S9 S10 have "x = A ⟶ 
       (𝟬 \<ls> x ⟶ A \<ls> x) ⟷ 
       (𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ A \<ls> A)" by (rule MMI_imbi12d)
   } then have S11: "∀ x.  x = A ⟶ 
       (𝟬 \<ls> x ⟶ A \<ls> x) ⟷ 
       (𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ A \<ls> A)" by simp
     from S11 have S12: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   (∀x∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> x ⟶ A \<ls> x) ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ A \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_rcla4v)
   from S8 S12 have S13: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> A ⟶ 
   (∀x∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> x ⟶ A \<ls> x) ⟶ A = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_syl5d)
   have S14: "A = 𝟬 ⟶ 
   (∀x∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> x ⟶ A \<ls> x) ⟶ A = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_ax_1)
   from S14 have S15: "𝟬 = A ⟶ 
   (∀x∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> x ⟶ A \<ls> x) ⟶ A = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_eqcoms)
   from S15 have S16: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 = A ⟶ 
   (∀x∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> x ⟶ A \<ls> x) ⟶ A = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_a1i)
   from S13 S16 have S17: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> A ∨ 𝟬 = A ⟶ 
   (∀x∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> x ⟶ A \<ls> x) ⟶ A = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_jaod)
   from S3 S17 have S18: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟶ 
   (∀x∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> x ⟶ A \<ls> x) ⟶ A = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_sylbid)
   from S18 show "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<lsq> A ∧ (∀x∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> x ⟶ A \<ls> x) ⟶ A = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_3imp)
qed

(********* 490 ************************************)

(*** this is proven by hand, bc the definition of complex 
    naturals is different in Metamath than in MMIsar0
    **********************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_peano5nn: assumes "A=A"
  shows "( 𝟭∈A ∧ (∀x∈A. x\<ca>𝟭 ∈ A ) ) ⟶ ℕ ⊆ A"
proof -
 { assume A1: "𝟭 ∈ A"  and A2: "∀x. x∈A ⟶ x\<ca>𝟭 ∈ A"
   let ?N = "A∩ℝ"
   have "?N ∈ Pow(ℝ)" by auto
   moreover from A1 have "𝟭 ∈ ?N" using MMI_ax1re by simp
   moreover from A2 have "∀n. n∈?N ⟶ n\<ca>𝟭 ∈ ?N"
     using MMI_ax1re MMI_axaddrcl by simp
   ultimately have "ℕ ⊆ A" using cxn_def by auto
 } then show ?thesis by simp
qed

(********* 491-497 *******************************)


lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_nnssre: 
   shows "ℕ ⊆ℝ"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   { fix x
     have "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ x \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_peano2re)
   } then have S2: "∀x. x ∈ ℝ ⟶ x \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by simp
   from S2 have S3: "∀x∈ℝ. x \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_rgen)
   have S4: "ℝ = ℝ" by (rule MMI_reex)
   from S4 have S5: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀x∈ℝ. x \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ) ⟶ ℕ ⊆ℝ" by (rule MMI_peano5nn)
   from S1 S3 S5 show "ℕ ⊆ℝ" by (rule MMI_mp2an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_nnsscn: 
   shows "ℕ ⊆ℂ"
proof -
   have S1: "ℕ ⊆ℝ" by (rule MMI_nnssre)
   have S2: "ℝ ⊆ℂ" by (rule MMI_axresscn)
   from S1 S2 show "ℕ ⊆ℂ" by (rule MMI_sstri)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_nnret: 
   shows "A ∈ ℕ ⟶ A ∈ ℝ"
proof -
   have S1: "ℕ ⊆ℝ" by (rule MMI_nnssre)
   from S1 show "A ∈ ℕ ⟶ A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_sseli)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_nncnt: 
   shows "A ∈ ℕ ⟶ A ∈ ℂ"
proof -
   have S1: "ℕ ⊆ℂ" by (rule MMI_nnsscn)
   from S1 show "A ∈ ℕ ⟶ A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_sseli)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_nnre: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℕ"   
   shows "A ∈ ℝ"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℕ".
   have S2: "A ∈ ℕ ⟶ A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_nnret)
   from S1 S2 show "A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax_mp)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_nncn: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℕ"   
   shows "A ∈ ℂ"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℕ".
   from S1 have S2: "A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_nnre)
   from S2 show "A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_nnex: 
   shows "ℕ = ℕ"
proof -
   have S1: "ℝ = ℝ" by (rule MMI_reex)
   have S2: "ℕ ⊆ℝ" by (rule MMI_nnssre)
   from S1 S2 show "ℕ = ℕ" by (rule MMI_ssexi)
qed

(********* 498,499 **************************
    proven by hand to get us to 500 without modifying 
    mmisar Haskell source - parsing Metamath 
    set comprehension is not supported yet.*)

lemma MMI_helper1: assumes "⋂K ≠ 0" shows "K≠0"
  using assms by auto

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_peano2nn:
  shows "x ∈ ℕ ⟶ x\<ca>𝟭 ∈ ℕ"
proof -
  let ?K = "{N ∈ Pow(ℝ). 𝟭 ∈ N ∧ (∀n. n∈N ⟶ n\<ca>𝟭 ∈ N)}"
  { assume A1: "x∈ℕ"
    then have "⋂?K ≠ 0" using cxn_def by auto
    then have "?K≠0" by (rule MMI_helper1)
    with A1 have "x\<ca>𝟭 ∈ ℕ" using cxn_def by auto
  } then show  "x ∈ ℕ ⟶ x\<ca>𝟭 ∈ ℕ" by simp
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_dfnn2: shows
  "ℕ = ⋂ {N ∈ Pow(ℝ). N ⊆ ℝ ∧ 𝟭∈N ∧ (∀n. n∈N ⟶ n\<ca>𝟭 ∈ N)}"
proof -
  let ?K⇩1 = "{N ∈ Pow(ℝ). N ⊆ ℝ ∧ 𝟭∈N ∧ (∀n. n∈N ⟶ n\<ca>𝟭 ∈ N)}"
  let ?K⇩2 = "{N ∈ Pow(ℝ). 𝟭∈N ∧ (∀n. n∈N ⟶ n\<ca>𝟭 ∈ N)}"
  have "?K⇩1 = ?K⇩2" by auto
  then show ?thesis using cxn_def by simp
qed
